39bool IsPartialBlit(const Context *context,
40 const FramebufferAttachment *readBuffer,
41 const FramebufferAttachment *writeBuffer,
42 GLint srcX0,
43 GLint srcY0,
44 GLint srcX1,
45 GLint srcY1,
46 GLint dstX0,
47 GLint dstY0,
48 GLint dstX1,
49 GLint dstY1)
50{
51 const Extents &writeSize = writeBuffer->getSize();
52 const Extents &readSize = readBuffer->getSize();
53
54 if (srcX0 != 0 || srcY0 != 0 || dstX0 != 0 || dstY0 != 0 || dstX1 != writeSize.width ||
55 dstY1 != writeSize.height || srcX1 != readSize.width || srcY1 != readSize.height)
56 {
57 return true;
58 }
59
60 if (context->getState().isScissorTestEnabled())
61 {
62 const Rectangle &scissor = context->getState().getScissor();
63 return scissor.x > 0 || scissor.y > 0 || scissor.width < writeSize.width ||
64 scissor.height < writeSize.height;
65 }
66
67 return false;
68}

70bool IsValidCopyTextureSourceInternalFormatEnum(GLenum internalFormat)
71{
72 // Table 1.1 from the CHROMIUM_copy_texture spec
73 switch (GetUnsizedFormat(internalFormat))
74 {
75 case GL_RED:
76 case GL_ALPHA:
77 case GL_LUMINANCE:
78 case GL_LUMINANCE_ALPHA:
79 case GL_RGB:
80 case GL_RGBA:
81 case GL_RGB8:
82 case GL_RGBA8:
83 case GL_BGRA_EXT:
84 case GL_BGRA8_EXT:
85 return true;
86
87 default:
88 return false;
89 }
90}

146
147bool IsValidCopyTextureDestinationFormatType(const Context *context,
148 GLint internalFormat,
149 GLenum type)
150{
151 if (!IsValidCopyTextureDestinationInternalFormatEnum(internalFormat))
152 {
153 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kInvalidInternalFormat);
154 return false;
155 }
156
157 if (!ValidES3FormatCombination(GetUnsizedFormat(internalFormat), type, internalFormat))
158 {
159 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kMismatchedTypeAndFormat);
160 return false;
161 }
162
163 const InternalFormat &internalFormatInfo = GetInternalFormatInfo(internalFormat, type);
164 if (!internalFormatInfo.textureSupport(context->getClientVersion(), context->getExtensions()))
165 {
166 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kInvalidInternalFormat);
167 return false;
168 }
169
170 return true;
171}

186 case TextureTarget::Rectangle:

188
189 default:
190 return false;
191 }
192}

218bool IsValidCopyTextureSourceLevel(const Context *context, TextureType type, GLint level)
219{
220 if (!ValidMipLevel(context, type, level))
221 {
222 return false;
223 }
224
225 if (level > 0 && context->getClientVersion() < ES_3_0)
226 {
227 return false;
228 }
229
230 return true;
231}
232
233bool IsValidCopyTextureDestinationLevel(const Context *context,
234 TextureType type,
235 GLint level,
236 GLsizei width,
237 GLsizei height,
238 bool isSubImage)
239{
240 if (!ValidMipLevel(context, type, level))
241 {
242 return false;
243 }
244
245 if (!ValidImageSizeParameters(context, type, level, width, height, 1, isSubImage))
246 {
247 return false;
248 }
249
250 const Caps &caps = context->getCaps();
251 switch (type)
252 {
253 case TextureType::_2D:
254 return width <= (caps.max2DTextureSize >> level) &&
255 height <= (caps.max2DTextureSize >> level);
256 case TextureType::Rectangle:
257 ASSERT(level == 0);
258 return width <= (caps.max2DTextureSize >> level) &&
259 height <= (caps.max2DTextureSize >> level);
260
261 case TextureType::CubeMap:
262 return width <= (caps.maxCubeMapTextureSize >> level) &&
263 height <= (caps.maxCubeMapTextureSize >> level);
264 default:
265 return true;
266 }
267}

321static inline bool Valid1to4ComponentFloatColorBufferFormat(const Context *context, GLenum format)
322{
323 return (context->getExtensions().textureFloatOES &&
324 (format == GL_RGBA32F || format == GL_RGB32F || format == GL_RG32F ||
325 format == GL_R32F)) ||
326 (context->getExtensions().textureHalfFloat &&
327 (format == GL_RGBA16F || format == GL_RGB16F || format == GL_RG16F ||
328 format == GL_R16F));
329}
330
331static inline bool Valid2to4ComponentFloatColorBufferFormat(const Context *context, GLenum format)
332{
333 return (context->getExtensions().textureFloatOES &&
334 (format == GL_RGBA32F || format == GL_RGB32F || format == GL_RG32F)) ||
335 (context->getExtensions().textureHalfFloat &&
336 (format == GL_RGBA16F || format == GL_RGB16F || format == GL_RG16F));
337}
338
339static inline bool Valid3to4ComponentFloatColorBufferFormat(const Context *context, GLenum format)
340{
341 return (context->getExtensions().textureFloatOES &&
342 (format == GL_RGBA32F || format == GL_RGB32F)) ||
343 (context->getExtensions().textureHalfFloat &&
344 (format == GL_RGBA16F || format == GL_RGB16F));
345}
346
347static inline bool Valid4ComponentFloatColorBufferFormat(const Context *context, GLenum format)
348{
349 return (context->getExtensions().textureFloatOES && format == GL_RGBA32F) ||
350 (context->getExtensions().textureHalfFloat && format == GL_RGBA16F);
351}

353bool ValidateES2CopyTexImageParameters(const Context *context,
354 TextureTarget target,
355 GLint level,
356 GLenum internalformat,
357 bool isSubImage,
358 GLint xoffset,
359 GLint yoffset,
360 GLint x,
361 GLint y,
362 GLsizei width,
363 GLsizei height,
364 GLint border)
365{
366 if (!ValidTexture2DDestinationTarget(context, target))
367 {
368 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kInvalidTextureTarget);
369 return false;
370 }
371
372 TextureType texType = TextureTargetToType(target);
373 if (!ValidImageSizeParameters(context, texType, level, width, height, 1, isSubImage))
374 {
375 // Error is already handled.
376 return false;
377 }
378
379 Format textureFormat = Format::Invalid();
380 if (!ValidateCopyTexImageParametersBase(context, target, level, internalformat, isSubImage,
381 xoffset, yoffset, 0, x, y, width, height, border,
382 &textureFormat))
383 {
384 return false;
385 }
386
387 const Framebuffer *framebuffer = context->getState().getReadFramebuffer();
388 GLenum colorbufferFormat =
389 framebuffer->getReadColorAttachment()->getFormat().info->sizedInternalFormat;
390 const auto &formatInfo = *textureFormat.info;
391
392 // [OpenGL ES 2.0.24] table 3.9
393 if (isSubImage)
394 {
395 switch (formatInfo.format)
396 {
397 case GL_ALPHA:
398 if (colorbufferFormat != GL_ALPHA8_EXT && colorbufferFormat != GL_RGBA4 &&
399 colorbufferFormat != GL_RGB5_A1 && colorbufferFormat != GL_RGBA8_OES &&
400 colorbufferFormat != GL_BGRA8_EXT && colorbufferFormat != GL_BGR5_A1_ANGLEX &&
401 !Valid4ComponentFloatColorBufferFormat(context, colorbufferFormat))
402 {
403 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kInvalidFormat);
404 return false;
405 }
406 break;
407 case GL_LUMINANCE:
408 if (colorbufferFormat != GL_R8_EXT && colorbufferFormat != GL_RG8_EXT &&
409 colorbufferFormat != GL_RGB565 && colorbufferFormat != GL_RGB8_OES &&
410 colorbufferFormat != GL_RGBA4 && colorbufferFormat != GL_RGB5_A1 &&
411 colorbufferFormat != GL_RGBA8_OES && colorbufferFormat != GL_BGRA8_EXT &&
412 colorbufferFormat != GL_BGR5_A1_ANGLEX &&
413 !Valid1to4ComponentFloatColorBufferFormat(context, colorbufferFormat))
414 {
415 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kInvalidFormat);
416 return false;
417 }
418 break;
419 case GL_RED_EXT:
420 if (colorbufferFormat != GL_R8_EXT && colorbufferFormat != GL_RG8_EXT &&
421 colorbufferFormat != GL_RGB565 && colorbufferFormat != GL_RGB8_OES &&
422 colorbufferFormat != GL_RGBA4 && colorbufferFormat != GL_RGB5_A1 &&
423 colorbufferFormat != GL_RGBA8_OES && colorbufferFormat != GL_R32F &&
424 colorbufferFormat != GL_RG32F && colorbufferFormat != GL_RGB32F &&
425 colorbufferFormat != GL_RGBA32F && colorbufferFormat != GL_BGRA8_EXT &&
426 colorbufferFormat != GL_BGR5_A1_ANGLEX &&
427 !Valid1to4ComponentFloatColorBufferFormat(context, colorbufferFormat))
428 {
429 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kInvalidFormat);
430 return false;
431 }
432 break;
433 case GL_RG_EXT:
434 if (colorbufferFormat != GL_RG8_EXT && colorbufferFormat != GL_RGB565 &&
435 colorbufferFormat != GL_RGB8_OES && colorbufferFormat != GL_RGBA4 &&
436 colorbufferFormat != GL_RGB5_A1 && colorbufferFormat != GL_RGBA8_OES &&
437 colorbufferFormat != GL_RG32F && colorbufferFormat != GL_RGB32F &&
438 colorbufferFormat != GL_RGBA32F && colorbufferFormat != GL_BGRA8_EXT &&
439 colorbufferFormat != GL_BGR5_A1_ANGLEX &&
440 !Valid2to4ComponentFloatColorBufferFormat(context, colorbufferFormat))
441 {
442 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kInvalidFormat);
443 return false;
444 }
445 break;
446 case GL_RGB:
447 if (colorbufferFormat != GL_RGB565 && colorbufferFormat != GL_RGB8_OES &&
448 colorbufferFormat != GL_RGBA4 && colorbufferFormat != GL_RGB5_A1 &&
449 colorbufferFormat != GL_RGBA8_OES && colorbufferFormat != GL_RGB32F &&
450 colorbufferFormat != GL_RGBA32F && colorbufferFormat != GL_BGRA8_EXT &&
451 colorbufferFormat != GL_BGR5_A1_ANGLEX &&
452 colorbufferFormat != GL_BGRX8_ANGLEX &&
453 !Valid3to4ComponentFloatColorBufferFormat(context, colorbufferFormat))
454 {
455 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kInvalidFormat);
456 return false;
457 }
458 break;
459 case GL_LUMINANCE_ALPHA:
460 case GL_RGBA:
461 if (colorbufferFormat != GL_RGBA4 && colorbufferFormat != GL_RGB5_A1 &&
462 colorbufferFormat != GL_RGBA8_OES && colorbufferFormat != GL_RGBA32F &&
463 colorbufferFormat != GL_BGRA8_EXT && colorbufferFormat != GL_BGR5_A1_ANGLEX &&
464 !Valid4ComponentFloatColorBufferFormat(context, colorbufferFormat))
465 {
466 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kInvalidFormat);
467 return false;
468 }
469 break;
470 case GL_COMPRESSED_RGB_S3TC_DXT1_EXT:
471 case GL_COMPRESSED_RGBA_S3TC_DXT1_EXT:
472 case GL_COMPRESSED_RGBA_S3TC_DXT3_ANGLE:
473 case GL_COMPRESSED_RGBA_S3TC_DXT5_ANGLE:
474 case GL_ETC1_RGB8_OES:
475 case GL_ETC1_RGB8_LOSSY_DECODE_ANGLE:
476 case GL_COMPRESSED_RGB8_LOSSY_DECODE_ETC2_ANGLE:
477 case GL_COMPRESSED_SRGB8_LOSSY_DECODE_ETC2_ANGLE:
478 case GL_COMPRESSED_RGB8_PUNCHTHROUGH_ALPHA1_LOSSY_DECODE_ETC2_ANGLE:
479 case GL_COMPRESSED_SRGB8_PUNCHTHROUGH_ALPHA1_LOSSY_DECODE_ETC2_ANGLE:
480 case GL_COMPRESSED_RGBA_BPTC_UNORM_EXT:
481 case GL_COMPRESSED_SRGB_ALPHA_BPTC_UNORM_EXT:
482 case GL_COMPRESSED_RGB_BPTC_SIGNED_FLOAT_EXT:
483 case GL_COMPRESSED_RGB_BPTC_UNSIGNED_FLOAT_EXT:
484 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kInvalidFormat);
485 return false;
486 case GL_DEPTH_COMPONENT:
487 case GL_DEPTH_STENCIL_OES:
488 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kInvalidFormat);
489 return false;
490 default:
491 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kInvalidFormat);
492 return false;
493 }
494
495 if (formatInfo.type == GL_FLOAT && !context->getExtensions().textureFloatOES)
496 {
497 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kInvalidFormat);
498 return false;
499 }
500 }
501 else
502 {
503 switch (internalformat)
504 {
505 case GL_ALPHA:
506 if (colorbufferFormat != GL_ALPHA8_EXT && colorbufferFormat != GL_RGBA4 &&
507 colorbufferFormat != GL_RGB5_A1 && colorbufferFormat != GL_BGRA8_EXT &&
508 colorbufferFormat != GL_RGBA8_OES && colorbufferFormat != GL_BGR5_A1_ANGLEX &&
509 !Valid4ComponentFloatColorBufferFormat(context, colorbufferFormat))
510 {
511 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kInvalidFormat);
512 return false;
513 }
514 break;
515 case GL_LUMINANCE:
516 case GL_RED_EXT:
517 if (colorbufferFormat != GL_R8_EXT && colorbufferFormat != GL_RG8_EXT &&
518 colorbufferFormat != GL_RGB565 && colorbufferFormat != GL_RGB8_OES &&
519 colorbufferFormat != GL_RGBA4 && colorbufferFormat != GL_RGB5_A1 &&
520 colorbufferFormat != GL_BGRA8_EXT && colorbufferFormat != GL_RGBA8_OES &&
521 colorbufferFormat != GL_BGR5_A1_ANGLEX &&
522 !Valid1to4ComponentFloatColorBufferFormat(context, colorbufferFormat))
523 {
524 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kInvalidFormat);
525 return false;
526 }
527 break;
528 case GL_RG_EXT:
529 if (colorbufferFormat != GL_RG8_EXT && colorbufferFormat != GL_RGB565 &&
530 colorbufferFormat != GL_RGB8_OES && colorbufferFormat != GL_RGBA4 &&
531 colorbufferFormat != GL_RGB5_A1 && colorbufferFormat != GL_BGRA8_EXT &&
532 colorbufferFormat != GL_RGBA8_OES && colorbufferFormat != GL_BGR5_A1_ANGLEX &&
533 !Valid2to4ComponentFloatColorBufferFormat(context, colorbufferFormat))
534 {
535 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kInvalidFormat);
536 return false;
537 }
538 break;
539 case GL_RGB:
540 if (colorbufferFormat != GL_RGB565 && colorbufferFormat != GL_RGB8_OES &&
541 colorbufferFormat != GL_RGBA4 && colorbufferFormat != GL_RGB5_A1 &&
542 colorbufferFormat != GL_BGRA8_EXT && colorbufferFormat != GL_RGBA8_OES &&
543 colorbufferFormat != GL_BGR5_A1_ANGLEX &&
544 !Valid3to4ComponentFloatColorBufferFormat(context, colorbufferFormat))
545 {
546 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kInvalidFormat);
547 return false;
548 }
549 break;
550 case GL_LUMINANCE_ALPHA:
551 case GL_RGBA:
552 if (colorbufferFormat != GL_RGBA4 && colorbufferFormat != GL_RGB5_A1 &&
553 colorbufferFormat != GL_BGRA8_EXT && colorbufferFormat != GL_RGBA8_OES &&
554 colorbufferFormat != GL_BGR5_A1_ANGLEX && colorbufferFormat != GL_RGBA16F &&
555 !Valid4ComponentFloatColorBufferFormat(context, colorbufferFormat))
556 {
557 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kInvalidFormat);
558 return false;
559 }
560 break;
561 case GL_COMPRESSED_RGB_S3TC_DXT1_EXT:
562 case GL_COMPRESSED_RGBA_S3TC_DXT1_EXT:
563 if (context->getExtensions().textureCompressionDXT1)
564 {
565 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kInvalidFormat);
566 return false;
567 }
568 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kEnumNotSupported);
569 return false;
570 case GL_COMPRESSED_RGBA_S3TC_DXT3_ANGLE:
571 if (context->getExtensions().textureCompressionDXT3)
572 {
573 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kInvalidFormat);
574 return false;
575 }
576 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kEnumNotSupported);
577 return false;
578 case GL_COMPRESSED_RGBA_S3TC_DXT5_ANGLE:
579 if (context->getExtensions().textureCompressionDXT5)
580 {
581 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kInvalidFormat);
582 return false;
583 }
584 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kEnumNotSupported);
585 return false;
586 case GL_ETC1_RGB8_OES:
587 if (context->getExtensions().compressedETC1RGB8TextureOES)
588 {
589 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kInvalidFormat);
590 return false;
591 }
592 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kEnumNotSupported);
593 return false;
594 case GL_ETC1_RGB8_LOSSY_DECODE_ANGLE:
595 case GL_COMPRESSED_RGB8_LOSSY_DECODE_ETC2_ANGLE:
596 case GL_COMPRESSED_SRGB8_LOSSY_DECODE_ETC2_ANGLE:
597 case GL_COMPRESSED_RGB8_PUNCHTHROUGH_ALPHA1_LOSSY_DECODE_ETC2_ANGLE:
598 case GL_COMPRESSED_SRGB8_PUNCHTHROUGH_ALPHA1_LOSSY_DECODE_ETC2_ANGLE:
599 if (context->getExtensions().lossyETCDecode)
600 {
601 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kInvalidFormat);
602 return false;
603 }
604 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kEnumNotSupported);
605 return false;
606 case GL_COMPRESSED_RGB_PVRTC_4BPPV1_IMG:
607 case GL_COMPRESSED_RGB_PVRTC_2BPPV1_IMG:
608 case GL_COMPRESSED_RGBA_PVRTC_4BPPV1_IMG:
609 case GL_COMPRESSED_RGBA_PVRTC_2BPPV1_IMG:
610 if (context->getExtensions().compressedTexturePVRTC)
611 {
612 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kInvalidFormat);
613 return false;
614 }
615 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kEnumNotSupported);
616 return false;
617 case GL_COMPRESSED_SRGB_PVRTC_2BPPV1_EXT:
618 case GL_COMPRESSED_SRGB_PVRTC_4BPPV1_EXT:
619 case GL_COMPRESSED_SRGB_ALPHA_PVRTC_2BPPV1_EXT:
620 case GL_COMPRESSED_SRGB_ALPHA_PVRTC_4BPPV1_EXT:
621 if (context->getExtensions().compressedTexturePVRTCsRGB)
622 {
623 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kInvalidFormat);
624 return false;
625 }
626 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kEnumNotSupported);
627 return false;
628 case GL_DEPTH_COMPONENT:
629 case GL_DEPTH_COMPONENT16:
630 case GL_DEPTH_COMPONENT32_OES:
631 if (context->getExtensions().depthTextureAny())
632 {
633 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kInvalidFormat);
634 return false;
635 }
636 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kEnumNotSupported);
637 return false;
638 case GL_DEPTH_STENCIL_OES:
639 case GL_DEPTH24_STENCIL8_OES:
640 if (context->getExtensions().depthTextureAny() ||
641 context->getExtensions().packedDepthStencilOES ||
642 context->getExtensions().depthTextureCubeMapOES)
643 {
644 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kInvalidFormat);
645 return false;
646 }
647 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kEnumNotSupported);
648 return false;
649 default:
650 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kEnumNotSupported);
651 return false;
652 }
653 }
654
655 // If width or height is zero, it is a no-op. Return false without setting an error.
656 return (width > 0 && height > 0);
657}

659bool ValidCap(const Context *context, GLenum cap, bool queryOnly)
660{
661 switch (cap)
662 {
663 // EXT_multisample_compatibility
664 case GL_MULTISAMPLE_EXT:
665 case GL_SAMPLE_ALPHA_TO_ONE_EXT:
666 return context->getExtensions().multisampleCompatibility;
667
668 case GL_CULL_FACE:
669 case GL_POLYGON_OFFSET_FILL:
670 case GL_SAMPLE_ALPHA_TO_COVERAGE:
671 case GL_SAMPLE_COVERAGE:
672 case GL_SCISSOR_TEST:
673 case GL_STENCIL_TEST:
674 case GL_DEPTH_TEST:
675 case GL_BLEND:
676 case GL_DITHER:
677 return true;
678
679 case GL_PRIMITIVE_RESTART_FIXED_INDEX:
680 case GL_RASTERIZER_DISCARD:
681 return (context->getClientMajorVersion() >= 3);
682
683 case GL_DEBUG_OUTPUT_SYNCHRONOUS:
684 case GL_DEBUG_OUTPUT:
685 return context->getExtensions().debug;
686
687 case GL_BIND_GENERATES_RESOURCE_CHROMIUM:
688 return queryOnly && context->getExtensions().bindGeneratesResource;
689
690 case GL_CLIENT_ARRAYS_ANGLE:
691 return queryOnly && context->getExtensions().clientArrays;
692
693 case GL_FRAMEBUFFER_SRGB_EXT:
694 return context->getExtensions().sRGBWriteControl;
695
696 case GL_SAMPLE_MASK:
697 return context->getClientVersion() >= Version(3, 1);
698
699 case GL_ROBUST_RESOURCE_INITIALIZATION_ANGLE:
700 return queryOnly && context->getExtensions().robustResourceInitialization;
701
702 case GL_TEXTURE_RECTANGLE_ANGLE:
703 return context->getExtensions().webglCompatibility;
704
705 // GL_APPLE_clip_distance/GL_EXT_clip_cull_distance
706 case GL_CLIP_DISTANCE0_EXT:
707 case GL_CLIP_DISTANCE1_EXT:
708 case GL_CLIP_DISTANCE2_EXT:
709 case GL_CLIP_DISTANCE3_EXT:
710 case GL_CLIP_DISTANCE4_EXT:
711 case GL_CLIP_DISTANCE5_EXT:
712 case GL_CLIP_DISTANCE6_EXT:
713 case GL_CLIP_DISTANCE7_EXT:
714 if (context->getClientVersion() >= Version(2, 0) &&
715 context->getExtensions().clipDistanceAPPLE)
716 {
717 return true;
718 }
719 break;
720 case GL_SAMPLE_SHADING:
721 return context->getExtensions().sampleShadingOES;
722 }
723
724 // GLES1 emulation: GLES1-specific caps after this point
725 if (context->getClientVersion().major != 1)
726 {
727 return false;
728 }
729
730 switch (cap)
731 {
732 case GL_ALPHA_TEST:
733 case GL_VERTEX_ARRAY:
734 case GL_NORMAL_ARRAY:
735 case GL_COLOR_ARRAY:
736 case GL_TEXTURE_COORD_ARRAY:
737 case GL_TEXTURE_2D:
738 case GL_LIGHTING:
739 case GL_LIGHT0:
740 case GL_LIGHT1:
741 case GL_LIGHT2:
742 case GL_LIGHT3:
743 case GL_LIGHT4:
744 case GL_LIGHT5:
745 case GL_LIGHT6:
746 case GL_LIGHT7:
747 case GL_NORMALIZE:
748 case GL_RESCALE_NORMAL:
749 case GL_COLOR_MATERIAL:
750 case GL_CLIP_PLANE0:
751 case GL_CLIP_PLANE1:
752 case GL_CLIP_PLANE2:
753 case GL_CLIP_PLANE3:
754 case GL_CLIP_PLANE4:
755 case GL_CLIP_PLANE5:
756 case GL_FOG:
757 case GL_POINT_SMOOTH:
758 case GL_LINE_SMOOTH:
759 case GL_COLOR_LOGIC_OP:
760 return context->getClientVersion() < Version(2, 0);
761 case GL_POINT_SIZE_ARRAY_OES:
762 return context->getClientVersion() < Version(2, 0) &&
763 context->getExtensions().pointSizeArrayOES;
764 case GL_TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP:
765 return context->getClientVersion() < Version(2, 0) &&
766 context->getExtensions().textureCubeMapOES;
767 case GL_POINT_SPRITE_OES:
768 return context->getClientVersion() < Version(2, 0) &&
769 context->getExtensions().pointSpriteOES;
770 default:
771 return false;
772 }
773}
774
775// Return true if a character belongs to the ASCII subset as defined in GLSL ES 1.0 spec section
776// 3.1.
777bool IsValidESSLCharacter(unsigned char c)
778{
779 // Printing characters are valid except " $ ` @ \ ' DEL.
780 if (c >= 32 && c <= 126 && c != '"' && c != '$' && c != '`' && c != '@' && c != '\\' &&
781 c != '\'')
782 {
783 return true;
784 }
785
786 // Horizontal tab, line feed, vertical tab, form feed, carriage return are also valid.
787 if (c >= 9 && c <= 13)
788 {
789 return true;
790 }
791
792 return false;
793}
794
795bool IsValidESSLString(const char *str, size_t len)
796{
797 for (size_t i = 0; i < len; i++)
798 {
799 if (!IsValidESSLCharacter(str[i]))
800 {
801 return false;
802 }
803 }
804
805 return true;
806}
807
808bool IsValidESSLShaderSourceString(const char *str, size_t len, bool lineContinuationAllowed)
809{
810 enum class ParseState
811 {
812 // Have not seen an ASCII non-whitespace character yet on
813 // this line. Possible that we might see a preprocessor
814 // directive.
815 BEGINING_OF_LINE,
816
817 // Have seen at least one ASCII non-whitespace character
818 // on this line.
819 MIDDLE_OF_LINE,
820
821 // Handling a preprocessor directive. Passes through all
822 // characters up to the end of the line. Disables comment
823 // processing.
824 IN_PREPROCESSOR_DIRECTIVE,
825
826 // Handling a single-line comment. The comment text is
827 // replaced with a single space.
828 IN_SINGLE_LINE_COMMENT,
829
830 // Handling a multi-line comment. Newlines are passed
831 // through to preserve line numbers.
832 IN_MULTI_LINE_COMMENT
833 };
834
835 ParseState state = ParseState::BEGINING_OF_LINE;
836 size_t pos = 0;
837
838 while (pos < len)
839 {
840 char c = str[pos];
841 char next = pos + 1 < len ? str[pos + 1] : 0;
842
843 // Check for newlines
844 if (c == '\n' || c == '\r')
845 {
846 if (state != ParseState::IN_MULTI_LINE_COMMENT)
847 {
848 state = ParseState::BEGINING_OF_LINE;
849 }
850
851 pos++;
852 continue;
853 }
854
855 switch (state)
856 {
857 case ParseState::BEGINING_OF_LINE:
858 if (c == ' ')
859 {
860 // Maintain the BEGINING_OF_LINE state until a non-space is seen
861 pos++;
862 }
863 else if (c == '#')
864 {
865 state = ParseState::IN_PREPROCESSOR_DIRECTIVE;
866 pos++;
867 }
868 else
869 {
870 // Don't advance, re-process this character with the MIDDLE_OF_LINE state
871 state = ParseState::MIDDLE_OF_LINE;
872 }
873 break;
874
875 case ParseState::MIDDLE_OF_LINE:
876 if (c == '/' && next == '/')
877 {
878 state = ParseState::IN_SINGLE_LINE_COMMENT;
879 pos++;
880 }
881 else if (c == '/' && next == '*')
882 {
883 state = ParseState::IN_MULTI_LINE_COMMENT;
884 pos++;
885 }
886 else if (lineContinuationAllowed && c == '\\' && (next == '\n' || next == '\r'))
887 {
888 // Skip line continuation characters
889 }
890 else if (!IsValidESSLCharacter(c))
891 {
892 return false;
893 }
894 pos++;
895 break;
896
897 case ParseState::IN_PREPROCESSOR_DIRECTIVE:
898 // Line-continuation characters may not be permitted.
899 // Otherwise, just pass it through. Do not parse comments in this state.
900 if (!lineContinuationAllowed && c == '\\')
901 {
902 return false;
903 }
904 pos++;
905 break;
906
907 case ParseState::IN_SINGLE_LINE_COMMENT:
908 // Line-continuation characters are processed before comment processing.
909 // Advance string if a new line character is immediately behind
910 // line-continuation character.
911 if (c == '\\' && (next == '\n' || next == '\r'))
912 {
913 pos++;
914 }
915 pos++;
916 break;
917
918 case ParseState::IN_MULTI_LINE_COMMENT:
919 if (c == '*' && next == '/')
920 {
921 state = ParseState::MIDDLE_OF_LINE;
922 pos++;
923 }
924 pos++;
925 break;
926 }
927 }
928
929 return true;
930}
931
932bool ValidateWebGLNamePrefix(const Context *context, const GLchar *name)
933{
934 ASSERT(context->isWebGL());
935
936 // WebGL 1.0 [Section 6.16] GLSL Constructs
937 // Identifiers starting with "webgl_" and "_webgl_" are reserved for use by WebGL.
938 if (strncmp(name, "webgl_", 6) == 0 || strncmp(name, "_webgl_", 7) == 0)
939 {
940 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kWebglBindAttribLocationReservedPrefix);
941 return false;
942 }
943
944 return true;
945}
946
947bool ValidateWebGLNameLength(const Context *context, size_t length)
948{
949 ASSERT(context->isWebGL());
950
951 if (context->isWebGL1() && length > 256)
952 {
953 // WebGL 1.0 [Section 6.21] Maxmimum Uniform and Attribute Location Lengths
954 // WebGL imposes a limit of 256 characters on the lengths of uniform and attribute
955 // locations.
956 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kWebglNameLengthLimitExceeded);
957
958 return false;
959 }
960 else if (length > 1024)
961 {
962 // WebGL 2.0 [Section 4.3.2] WebGL 2.0 imposes a limit of 1024 characters on the lengths of
963 // uniform and attribute locations.
964 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kWebgl2NameLengthLimitExceeded);
965 return false;
966 }
967
968 return true;
969}

971bool ValidBlendFunc(const Context *context, GLenum val)
972{
973 const Extensions &ext = context->getExtensions();
974
975 // these are always valid for src and dst.
976 switch (val)
977 {
978 case GL_ZERO:
979 case GL_ONE:
980 case GL_SRC_COLOR:
981 case GL_ONE_MINUS_SRC_COLOR:
982 case GL_DST_COLOR:
983 case GL_ONE_MINUS_DST_COLOR:
984 case GL_SRC_ALPHA:
985 case GL_ONE_MINUS_SRC_ALPHA:
986 case GL_DST_ALPHA:
987 case GL_ONE_MINUS_DST_ALPHA:
988 case GL_CONSTANT_COLOR:
989 case GL_ONE_MINUS_CONSTANT_COLOR:
990 case GL_CONSTANT_ALPHA:
991 case GL_ONE_MINUS_CONSTANT_ALPHA:
992 return true;
993
994 // EXT_blend_func_extended.
995 case GL_SRC1_COLOR_EXT:
996 case GL_SRC1_ALPHA_EXT:
997 case GL_ONE_MINUS_SRC1_COLOR_EXT:
998 case GL_ONE_MINUS_SRC1_ALPHA_EXT:
999 case GL_SRC_ALPHA_SATURATE_EXT:
1000 return ext.blendFuncExtended;
1001
1002 default:
1003 return false;
1004 }
1005}
1006
1007bool ValidSrcBlendFunc(const Context *context, GLenum val)
1008{
1009 if (ValidBlendFunc(context, val))
1010 return true;
1011
1012 if (val == GL_SRC_ALPHA_SATURATE)
1013 return true;
1014
1015 return false;
1016}
1017
1018bool ValidDstBlendFunc(const Context *context, GLenum val)
1019{
1020 if (ValidBlendFunc(context, val))
1021 return true;
1022
1023 if (val == GL_SRC_ALPHA_SATURATE)
1024 {
1025 if (context->getClientMajorVersion() >= 3)
1026 return true;
1027 }
1028
1029 return false;
1030}

1055 isSubImage, xoffset, yoffset, width, height, border,

1059} // anonymous namespace
1060
1061bool ValidateES2TexImageParametersBase(const Context *context,
1062 TextureTarget target,
1063 GLint level,
1064 GLenum internalformat,
1065 bool isCompressed,
1066 bool isSubImage,
1067 GLint xoffset,
1068 GLint yoffset,
1069 GLsizei width,
1070 GLsizei height,
1071 GLint border,
1072 GLenum format,
1073 GLenum type,
1074 GLsizei imageSize,
1075 const void *pixels)
1076{
1077
1078 TextureType texType = TextureTargetToType(target);
1079 if (!ValidImageSizeParameters(context, texType, level, width, height, 1, isSubImage))
1080 {
1081 // Error already handled.
1082 return false;
1083 }
1084
1085 if (!ValidMipLevel(context, texType, level))
1086 {
1087 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kInvalidMipLevel);
1088 return false;
1089 }
1090
1091 if (xoffset < 0 || std::numeric_limits<GLsizei>::max() - xoffset < width ||
1092 std::numeric_limits<GLsizei>::max() - yoffset < height)
1093 {
1094 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kResourceMaxTextureSize);
1095 return false;
1096 }
1097
1098 const Caps &caps = context->getCaps();
1099
1100 switch (texType)
1101 {
1102 case TextureType::_2D:
1103 case TextureType::External:
1104 case TextureType::VideoImage:
1105 if (width > (caps.max2DTextureSize >> level) ||
1106 height > (caps.max2DTextureSize >> level))
1107 {
1108 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kResourceMaxTextureSize);
1109 return false;
1110 }
1111 break;
1112
1113 case TextureType::Rectangle:
1114 ASSERT(level == 0);
1115 if (width > caps.maxRectangleTextureSize || height > caps.maxRectangleTextureSize)
1116 {
1117 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kResourceMaxTextureSize);
1118 return false;
1119 }
1120 if (isCompressed)
1121 {
1122 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kRectangleTextureCompressed);
1123 return false;
1124 }
1125 break;
1126
1127 case TextureType::CubeMap:
1128 if (!isSubImage && width != height)
1129 {
1130 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kCubemapFacesEqualDimensions);
1131 return false;
1132 }
1133
1134 if (width > (caps.maxCubeMapTextureSize >> level) ||
1135 height > (caps.maxCubeMapTextureSize >> level))
1136 {
1137 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kResourceMaxTextureSize);
1138 return false;
1139 }
1140 break;
1141
1142 default:
1143 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kInvalidTextureTarget);
1144 return false;
1145 }
1146
1147 Texture *texture = context->getTextureByType(texType);
1148 if (!texture)
1149 {
1150 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kBufferNotBound);
1151 return false;
1152 }
1153
1154 // Verify zero border
1155 if (border != 0)
1156 {
1157 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kInvalidBorder);
1158 return false;
1159 }
1160
1161 bool nonEqualFormatsAllowed = false;
1162
1163 if (isCompressed)
1164 {
1165 GLenum actualInternalFormat =
1166 isSubImage ? texture->getFormat(target, level).info->sizedInternalFormat
1167 : internalformat;
1168
1169 const InternalFormat &internalFormatInfo = GetSizedInternalFormatInfo(actualInternalFormat);
1170
1171 if (!internalFormatInfo.compressed)
1172 {
1173 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kInvalidInternalFormat);
1174 return false;
1175 }
1176
1177 if (!internalFormatInfo.textureSupport(context->getClientVersion(),
1178 context->getExtensions()))
1179 {
1180 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kInvalidInternalFormat);
1181 return false;
1182 }
1183
1184 if (isSubImage)
1185 {
1186 // From the OES_compressed_ETC1_RGB8_texture spec:
1187 //
1188 // INVALID_OPERATION is generated by CompressedTexSubImage2D, TexSubImage2D, or
1189 // CopyTexSubImage2D if the texture image <level> bound to <target> has internal format
1190 // ETC1_RGB8_OES.
1191 //
1192 // This is relaxed if GL_EXT_compressed_ETC1_RGB8_sub_texture is supported.
1193 if (actualInternalFormat == GL_ETC1_RGB8_OES &&
1194 !context->getExtensions().compressedETC1RGB8SubTexture)
1195 {
1196 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kInvalidInternalFormat);
1197 return false;
1198 }
1199
1200 if (!ValidCompressedSubImageSize(context, actualInternalFormat, xoffset, yoffset, 0,
1201 width, height, 1, texture->getWidth(target, level),
1202 texture->getHeight(target, level),
1203 texture->getDepth(target, level)))
1204 {
1205 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kInvalidCompressedImageSize);
1206 return false;
1207 }
1208
1209 if (format != actualInternalFormat)
1210 {
1211 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kInvalidFormat);
1212 return false;
1213 }
1214 }
1215 else
1216 {
1217 if (!ValidCompressedImageSize(context, actualInternalFormat, level, width, height, 1))
1218 {
1219 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kInvalidCompressedImageSize);
1220 return false;
1221 }
1222 }
1223 }
1224 else
1225 {
1226 // validate <type> by itself (used as secondary key below)
1227 switch (type)
1228 {
1229 case GL_UNSIGNED_BYTE:
1230 case GL_UNSIGNED_SHORT_5_6_5:
1231 case GL_UNSIGNED_SHORT_4_4_4_4:
1232 case GL_UNSIGNED_SHORT_5_5_5_1:
1233 case GL_UNSIGNED_SHORT:
1234 case GL_UNSIGNED_INT:
1235 case GL_UNSIGNED_INT_24_8_OES:
1236 case GL_HALF_FLOAT_OES:
1237 case GL_FLOAT:
1238 break;
1239 case GL_UNSIGNED_INT_2_10_10_10_REV_EXT:
1240 if (!context->getExtensions().textureFormat2101010REV)
1241 {
1242 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kEnumNotSupported);
1243 return false;
1244 }
1245 break;
1246 default:
1247 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kInvalidType);
1248 return false;
1249 }
1250
1251 // validate <format> + <type> combinations
1252 // - invalid <format> -> sets INVALID_ENUM
1253 // - invalid <format>+<type> combination -> sets INVALID_OPERATION
1254 switch (format)
1255 {
1256 case GL_ALPHA:
1257 case GL_LUMINANCE:
1258 case GL_LUMINANCE_ALPHA:
1259 switch (type)
1260 {
1261 case GL_UNSIGNED_BYTE:
1262 case GL_FLOAT:
1263 case GL_HALF_FLOAT_OES:
1264 break;
1265 default:
1266 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kMismatchedTypeAndFormat);
1267 return false;
1268 }
1269 break;
1270 case GL_RED:
1271 case GL_RG:
1272 if (!context->getExtensions().textureRG)
1273 {
1274 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kEnumNotSupported);
1275 return false;
1276 }
1277 switch (type)
1278 {
1279 case GL_UNSIGNED_BYTE:
1280 break;
1281 case GL_FLOAT:
1282 if (!context->getExtensions().textureFloatOES)
1283 {
1284 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kEnumNotSupported);
1285 return false;
1286 }
1287 break;
1288 case GL_HALF_FLOAT_OES:
1289 if (!context->getExtensions().textureFloatOES &&
1290 !context->getExtensions().textureHalfFloat)
1291 {
1292 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kEnumNotSupported);
1293 return false;
1294 }
1295 break;
1296 case GL_SHORT:
1297 case GL_UNSIGNED_SHORT:
1298 if (!context->getExtensions().textureNorm16)
1299 {
1300 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kEnumNotSupported);
1301 return false;
1302 }
1303 break;
1304 default:
1305 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kMismatchedTypeAndFormat);
1306 return false;
1307 }
1308 break;
1309 case GL_RGB:
1310 switch (type)
1311 {
1312 case GL_UNSIGNED_BYTE:
1313 case GL_UNSIGNED_SHORT_5_6_5:
1314 case GL_UNSIGNED_INT_2_10_10_10_REV_EXT:
1315 case GL_FLOAT:
1316 case GL_HALF_FLOAT_OES:
1317 break;
1318 case GL_SHORT:
1319 case GL_UNSIGNED_SHORT:
1320 if (!context->getExtensions().textureNorm16)
1321 {
1322 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION,
1323 kMismatchedTypeAndFormat);
1324 return false;
1325 }
1326 break;
1327 default:
1328 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kMismatchedTypeAndFormat);
1329 return false;
1330 }
1331 break;
1332 case GL_RGBA:
1333 switch (type)
1334 {
1335 case GL_UNSIGNED_BYTE:
1336 case GL_UNSIGNED_SHORT_4_4_4_4:
1337 case GL_UNSIGNED_SHORT_5_5_5_1:
1338 case GL_FLOAT:
1339 case GL_HALF_FLOAT_OES:
1340 case GL_UNSIGNED_INT_2_10_10_10_REV_EXT:
1341 break;
1342 case GL_SHORT:
1343 case GL_UNSIGNED_SHORT:
1344 if (!context->getExtensions().textureNorm16)
1345 {
1346 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION,
1347 kMismatchedTypeAndFormat);
1348 return false;
1349 }
1350 break;
1351 default:
1352 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kMismatchedTypeAndFormat);
1353 return false;
1354 }
1355 break;
1356 case GL_BGRA_EXT:
1357 if (!context->getExtensions().textureFormatBGRA8888)
1358 {
1359 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kEnumNotSupported);
1360 return false;
1361 }
1362 switch (type)
1363 {
1364 case GL_UNSIGNED_BYTE:
1365 break;
1366 default:
1367 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kMismatchedTypeAndFormat);
1368 return false;
1369 }
1370 break;
1371 case GL_SRGB_EXT:
1372 case GL_SRGB_ALPHA_EXT:
1373 if (!context->getExtensions().sRGB)
1374 {
1375 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kEnumNotSupported);
1376 return false;
1377 }
1378 switch (type)
1379 {
1380 case GL_UNSIGNED_BYTE:
1381 break;
1382 default:
1383 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kMismatchedTypeAndFormat);
1384 return false;
1385 }
1386 break;
1387 case GL_COMPRESSED_RGB_S3TC_DXT1_EXT: // error cases for compressed textures are
1388 // handled below
1389 case GL_COMPRESSED_RGBA_S3TC_DXT1_EXT:
1390 case GL_COMPRESSED_RGBA_S3TC_DXT3_ANGLE:
1391 case GL_COMPRESSED_RGBA_S3TC_DXT5_ANGLE:
1392 break;
1393 case GL_DEPTH_COMPONENT:
1394 switch (type)
1395 {
1396 case GL_UNSIGNED_SHORT:
1397 case GL_UNSIGNED_INT:
1398 break;
1399 case GL_FLOAT:
1400 if (!context->getExtensions().depthBufferFloat2NV)
1401 {
1402 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION,
1403 kMismatchedTypeAndFormat);
1404 return false;
1405 }
1406 break;
1407 default:
1408 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kMismatchedTypeAndFormat);
1409 return false;
1410 }
1411 break;
1412 case GL_DEPTH_STENCIL_OES:
1413 switch (type)
1414 {
1415 case GL_UNSIGNED_INT_24_8_OES:
1416 break;
1417 default:
1418 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kMismatchedTypeAndFormat);
1419 return false;
1420 }
1421 break;
1422 case GL_STENCIL_INDEX:
1423 switch (type)
1424 {
1425 case GL_UNSIGNED_BYTE:
1426 break;
1427 default:
1428 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kMismatchedTypeAndFormat);
1429 return false;
1430 }
1431 break;
1432 default:
1433 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kEnumNotSupported);
1434 return false;
1435 }
1436
1437 switch (format)
1438 {
1439 case GL_COMPRESSED_RGB_S3TC_DXT1_EXT:
1440 case GL_COMPRESSED_RGBA_S3TC_DXT1_EXT:
1441 if (context->getExtensions().textureCompressionDXT1)
1442 {
1443 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kInvalidFormat);
1444 return false;
1445 }
1446 else
1447 {
1448 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kEnumNotSupported);
1449 return false;
1450 }
1451 break;
1452 case GL_COMPRESSED_RGBA_S3TC_DXT3_ANGLE:
1453 if (context->getExtensions().textureCompressionDXT3)
1454 {
1455 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kInvalidFormat);
1456 return false;
1457 }
1458 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kEnumNotSupported);
1459 return false;
1460 case GL_COMPRESSED_RGBA_S3TC_DXT5_ANGLE:
1461 if (context->getExtensions().textureCompressionDXT5)
1462 {
1463 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kInvalidFormat);
1464 return false;
1465 }
1466 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kEnumNotSupported);
1467 return false;
1468 case GL_ETC1_RGB8_OES:
1469 if (context->getExtensions().compressedETC1RGB8TextureOES)
1470 {
1471 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kInvalidFormat);
1472 return false;
1473 }
1474 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kEnumNotSupported);
1475 return false;
1476 case GL_ETC1_RGB8_LOSSY_DECODE_ANGLE:
1477 case GL_COMPRESSED_RGB8_LOSSY_DECODE_ETC2_ANGLE:
1478 case GL_COMPRESSED_SRGB8_LOSSY_DECODE_ETC2_ANGLE:
1479 case GL_COMPRESSED_RGB8_PUNCHTHROUGH_ALPHA1_LOSSY_DECODE_ETC2_ANGLE:
1480 case GL_COMPRESSED_SRGB8_PUNCHTHROUGH_ALPHA1_LOSSY_DECODE_ETC2_ANGLE:
1481 if (context->getExtensions().lossyETCDecode)
1482 {
1483 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kInvalidFormat);
1484 return false;
1485 }
1486 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kEnumNotSupported);
1487 return false;
1488 case GL_COMPRESSED_RGB_PVRTC_4BPPV1_IMG:
1489 case GL_COMPRESSED_RGB_PVRTC_2BPPV1_IMG:
1490 case GL_COMPRESSED_RGBA_PVRTC_4BPPV1_IMG:
1491 case GL_COMPRESSED_RGBA_PVRTC_2BPPV1_IMG:
1492 if (context->getExtensions().compressedTexturePVRTC)
1493 {
1494 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kInvalidFormat);
1495 return false;
1496 }
1497 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kEnumNotSupported);
1498 return false;
1499 case GL_COMPRESSED_SRGB_PVRTC_2BPPV1_EXT:
1500 case GL_COMPRESSED_SRGB_PVRTC_4BPPV1_EXT:
1501 case GL_COMPRESSED_SRGB_ALPHA_PVRTC_2BPPV1_EXT:
1502 case GL_COMPRESSED_SRGB_ALPHA_PVRTC_4BPPV1_EXT:
1503 if (context->getExtensions().compressedTexturePVRTCsRGB)
1504 {
1505 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kInvalidFormat);
1506 return false;
1507 }
1508 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kEnumNotSupported);
1509 return false;
1510 case GL_DEPTH_COMPONENT:
1511 case GL_DEPTH_STENCIL_OES:
1512 if (!context->getExtensions().depthTextureANGLE &&
1513 !((context->getExtensions().packedDepthStencilOES ||
1514 context->getExtensions().depthTextureCubeMapOES) &&
1515 context->getExtensions().depthTextureOES))
1516 {
1517 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kEnumNotSupported);
1518 return false;
1519 }
1520
1521 switch (target)
1522 {
1523 case TextureTarget::_2D:
1524 break;
1525 case TextureTarget::CubeMapNegativeX:
1526 case TextureTarget::CubeMapNegativeY:
1527 case TextureTarget::CubeMapNegativeZ:
1528 case TextureTarget::CubeMapPositiveX:
1529 case TextureTarget::CubeMapPositiveY:
1530 case TextureTarget::CubeMapPositiveZ:
1531 if (!context->getExtensions().depthTextureCubeMapOES)
1532 {
1533 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION,
1534 kMismatchedTargetAndFormat);
1535 return false;
1536 }
1537 break;
1538 default:
1539 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kMismatchedTargetAndFormat);
1540 return false;
1541 }
1542
1543 // OES_depth_texture supports loading depth data and multiple levels,
1544 // but ANGLE_depth_texture does not
1545 if (!context->getExtensions().depthTextureOES)
1546 {
1547 if (pixels != nullptr)
1548 {
1549 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kPixelDataNotNull);
1550 return false;
1551 }
1552 if (level != 0)
1553 {
1554 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kLevelNotZero);
1555 return false;
1556 }
1557 }
1558 break;
1559 case GL_STENCIL_INDEX:
1560 if (!context->getExtensions().stencilIndex8)
1561 {
1562 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kInvalidFormat);
1563 return false;
1564 }
1565
1566 switch (target)
1567 {
1568 case TextureTarget::_2D:
1569 case TextureTarget::_2DArray:
1570 case TextureTarget::CubeMapNegativeX:
1571 case TextureTarget::CubeMapNegativeY:
1572 case TextureTarget::CubeMapNegativeZ:
1573 case TextureTarget::CubeMapPositiveX:
1574 case TextureTarget::CubeMapPositiveY:
1575 case TextureTarget::CubeMapPositiveZ:
1576 break;
1577 default:
1578 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kMismatchedTargetAndFormat);
1579 return false;
1580 }
1581
1582 if (internalformat != GL_STENCIL_INDEX8)
1583 {
1584 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kMismatchedTargetAndFormat);
1585 return false;
1586 }
1587 break;
1588 default:
1589 break;
1590 }
1591
1592 if (!isSubImage)
1593 {
1594 switch (internalformat)
1595 {
1596 // Core ES 2.0 formats
1597 case GL_ALPHA:
1598 case GL_LUMINANCE:
1599 case GL_LUMINANCE_ALPHA:
1600 case GL_RGB:
1601 case GL_RGBA:
1602 break;
1603
1604 case GL_RGBA32F:
1605 if (!context->getExtensions().colorBufferFloatRGBA)
1606 {
1607 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kInvalidFormat);
1608 return false;
1609 }
1610
1611 nonEqualFormatsAllowed = true;
1612
1613 if (type != GL_FLOAT)
1614 {
1615 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kMismatchedTypeAndFormat);
1616 return false;
1617 }
1618 if (format != GL_RGBA)
1619 {
1620 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kMismatchedTypeAndFormat);
1621 return false;
1622 }
1623 break;
1624
1625 case GL_RGB32F:
1626 if (!context->getExtensions().colorBufferFloatRGB)
1627 {
1628 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kInvalidFormat);
1629 return false;
1630 }
1631
1632 nonEqualFormatsAllowed = true;
1633
1634 if (type != GL_FLOAT)
1635 {
1636 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kMismatchedTypeAndFormat);
1637 return false;
1638 }
1639 if (format != GL_RGB)
1640 {
1641 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kMismatchedTypeAndFormat);
1642 return false;
1643 }
1644 break;
1645
1646 case GL_BGRA_EXT:
1647 if (!context->getExtensions().textureFormatBGRA8888)
1648 {
1649 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kInvalidFormat);
1650 return false;
1651 }
1652 break;
1653
1654 case GL_DEPTH_COMPONENT:
1655 if (!(context->getExtensions().depthTextureAny()))
1656 {
1657 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kInvalidFormat);
1658 return false;
1659 }
1660 break;
1661
1662 case GL_DEPTH_STENCIL:
1663 if (!(context->getExtensions().depthTextureANGLE ||
1664 context->getExtensions().packedDepthStencilOES ||
1665 context->getExtensions().depthTextureCubeMapOES))
1666 {
1667 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kInvalidFormat);
1668 return false;
1669 }
1670 break;
1671
1672 case GL_STENCIL_INDEX8:
1673 if (!context->getExtensions().stencilIndex8)
1674 {
1675 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kInvalidFormat);
1676 return false;
1677 }
1678 break;
1679
1680 case GL_RED:
1681 case GL_RG:
1682 if (!context->getExtensions().textureRG)
1683 {
1684 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kInvalidFormat);
1685 return false;
1686 }
1687 break;
1688
1689 case GL_SRGB_EXT:
1690 case GL_SRGB_ALPHA_EXT:
1691 if (!context->getExtensions().sRGB)
1692 {
1693 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kEnumNotSupported);
1694 return false;
1695 }
1696 break;
1697
1698 case GL_RGB10_A2_EXT:
1699 if (!context->getExtensions().textureFormat2101010REV)
1700 {
1701 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kEnumNotSupported);
1702 return false;
1703 }
1704
1705 if (type != GL_UNSIGNED_INT_2_10_10_10_REV_EXT || format != GL_RGBA)
1706 {
1707 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kMismatchedTypeAndFormat);
1708 return false;
1709 }
1710
1711 nonEqualFormatsAllowed = true;
1712
1713 break;
1714
1715 case GL_RGB5_A1:
1716 if (context->getExtensions().textureFormat2101010REV &&
1717 type == GL_UNSIGNED_INT_2_10_10_10_REV_EXT && format == GL_RGBA)
1718 {
1719 nonEqualFormatsAllowed = true;
1720 }
1721
1722 break;
1723
1724 case GL_R16_EXT:
1725 case GL_RG16_EXT:
1726 case GL_RGB16_EXT:
1727 case GL_RGBA16_EXT:
1728 case GL_R16_SNORM_EXT:
1729 case GL_RG16_SNORM_EXT:
1730 case GL_RGB16_SNORM_EXT:
1731 case GL_RGBA16_SNORM_EXT:
1732 if (!context->getExtensions().textureNorm16)
1733 {
1734 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kEnumNotSupported);
1735 return false;
1736 }
1737 break;
1738 default:
1739 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kInvalidInternalFormat);
1740 return false;
1741 }
1742 }
1743
1744 if (type == GL_FLOAT)
1745 {
1746 if (!context->getExtensions().textureFloatOES)
1747 {
1748 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kEnumNotSupported);
1749 return false;
1750 }
1751 }
1752 else if (type == GL_HALF_FLOAT_OES)
1753 {
1754 if (!context->getExtensions().textureHalfFloat)
1755 {
1756 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kEnumNotSupported);
1757 return false;
1758 }
1759 }
1760 }
1761
1762 if (isSubImage)
1763 {
1764 const InternalFormat &textureInternalFormat = *texture->getFormat(target, level).info;
1765 if (textureInternalFormat.internalFormat == GL_NONE)
1766 {
1767 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kInvalidTextureLevel);
1768 return false;
1769 }
1770
1771 if (format != textureInternalFormat.format)
1772 {
1773 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, err::kTextureFormatMismatch);
1774 return false;
1775 }
1776
1777 if (context->getExtensions().webglCompatibility)
1778 {
1779 if (GetInternalFormatInfo(format, type).sizedInternalFormat !=
1780 textureInternalFormat.sizedInternalFormat)
1781 {
1782 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kTextureTypeMismatch);
1783 return false;
1784 }
1785 }
1786
1787 if (static_cast<size_t>(xoffset + width) > texture->getWidth(target, level) ||
1788 static_cast<size_t>(yoffset + height) > texture->getHeight(target, level))
1789 {
1790 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kOffsetOverflow);
1791 return false;
1792 }
1793
1794 if (width > 0 && height > 0 && pixels == nullptr &&
1795 context->getState().getTargetBuffer(BufferBinding::PixelUnpack) == nullptr)
1796 {
1797 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kPixelDataNull);
1798 return false;
1799 }
1800 }
1801 else
1802 {
1803 if (texture->getImmutableFormat())
1804 {
1805 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kTextureIsImmutable);
1806 return false;
1807 }
1808 }
1809
1810 // From GL_CHROMIUM_color_buffer_float_rgb[a]:
1811 // GL_RGB[A] / GL_RGB[A]32F becomes an allowable format / internalformat parameter pair for
1812 // TexImage2D. The restriction in section 3.7.1 of the OpenGL ES 2.0 spec that the
1813 // internalformat parameter and format parameter of TexImage2D must match is lifted for this
1814 // case.
1815 if (!isSubImage && !isCompressed && internalformat != format && !nonEqualFormatsAllowed)
1816 {
1817 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kInvalidFormatCombination);
1818 return false;
1819 }
1820
1821 GLenum sizeCheckFormat = isSubImage ? format : internalformat;
1822 return ValidImageDataSize(context, texType, width, height, 1, sizeCheckFormat, type, pixels,
1823 imageSize);
1824}

1826bool ValidateES2TexStorageParametersBase(const Context *context,
1827 TextureType target,
1828 GLsizei levels,
1829 GLenum internalformat,
1830 GLsizei width,
1831 GLsizei height)
1832{
1833 if (target != TextureType::_2D && target != TextureType::CubeMap &&
1834 target != TextureType::Rectangle)
1835 {
1836 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kInvalidTextureTarget);
1837 return false;
1838 }
1839
1840 if (width < 1 || height < 1 || levels < 1)
1841 {
1842 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kTextureSizeTooSmall);
1843 return false;
1844 }
1845
1846 if (target == TextureType::CubeMap && width != height)
1847 {
1848 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kCubemapFacesEqualDimensions);
1849 return false;
1850 }
1851
1852 if (levels != 1 && levels != log2(std::max(width, height)) + 1)
1853 {
1854 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kInvalidMipLevels);
1855 return false;
1856 }
1857
1858 const InternalFormat &formatInfo = GetSizedInternalFormatInfo(internalformat);
1859 if (formatInfo.format == GL_NONE || formatInfo.type == GL_NONE)
1860 {
1861 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kInvalidFormat);
1862 return false;
1863 }
1864
1865 const Caps &caps = context->getCaps();
1866
1867 switch (target)
1868 {
1869 case TextureType::_2D:
1870 if (width > caps.max2DTextureSize || height > caps.max2DTextureSize)
1871 {
1872 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kResourceMaxTextureSize);
1873 return false;
1874 }
1875 break;
1876 case TextureType::Rectangle:
1877 if (levels != 1)
1878 {
1879 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kInvalidMipLevel);
1880 return false;
1881 }
1882
1883 if (width > caps.maxRectangleTextureSize || height > caps.maxRectangleTextureSize)
1884 {
1885 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kResourceMaxTextureSize);
1886 return false;
1887 }
1888 if (formatInfo.compressed)
1889 {
1890 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kRectangleTextureCompressed);
1891 return false;
1892 }
1893 break;
1894 case TextureType::CubeMap:
1895 if (width > caps.maxCubeMapTextureSize || height > caps.maxCubeMapTextureSize)
1896 {
1897 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kResourceMaxTextureSize);
1898 return false;
1899 }
1900 break;
1901 default:
1902 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kEnumNotSupported);
1903 return false;
1904 }
1905
1906 if (levels != 1 && !context->getExtensions().textureNPOTOES)
1907 {
1908 if (!isPow2(width) || !isPow2(height))
1909 {
1910 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kDimensionsMustBePow2);
1911 return false;
1912 }
1913 }
1914
1915 switch (internalformat)
1916 {
1917 case GL_COMPRESSED_RGB_S3TC_DXT1_EXT:
1918 case GL_COMPRESSED_RGBA_S3TC_DXT1_EXT:
1919 if (!context->getExtensions().textureCompressionDXT1)
1920 {
1921 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kEnumNotSupported);
1922 return false;
1923 }
1924 break;
1925 case GL_COMPRESSED_RGBA_S3TC_DXT3_ANGLE:
1926 if (!context->getExtensions().textureCompressionDXT3)
1927 {
1928 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kEnumNotSupported);
1929 return false;
1930 }
1931 break;
1932 case GL_COMPRESSED_RGBA_S3TC_DXT5_ANGLE:
1933 if (!context->getExtensions().textureCompressionDXT5)
1934 {
1935 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kEnumNotSupported);
1936 return false;
1937 }
1938 break;
1939 case GL_ETC1_RGB8_OES:
1940 if (!context->getExtensions().compressedETC1RGB8TextureOES)
1941 {
1942 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kEnumNotSupported);
1943 return false;
1944 }
1945 break;
1946 case GL_ETC1_RGB8_LOSSY_DECODE_ANGLE:
1947 case GL_COMPRESSED_RGB8_LOSSY_DECODE_ETC2_ANGLE:
1948 case GL_COMPRESSED_SRGB8_LOSSY_DECODE_ETC2_ANGLE:
1949 case GL_COMPRESSED_RGB8_PUNCHTHROUGH_ALPHA1_LOSSY_DECODE_ETC2_ANGLE:
1950 case GL_COMPRESSED_SRGB8_PUNCHTHROUGH_ALPHA1_LOSSY_DECODE_ETC2_ANGLE:
1951 if (!context->getExtensions().lossyETCDecode)
1952 {
1953 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kEnumNotSupported);
1954 return false;
1955 }
1956 break;
1957 case GL_COMPRESSED_RGB_PVRTC_4BPPV1_IMG:
1958 case GL_COMPRESSED_RGB_PVRTC_2BPPV1_IMG:
1959 case GL_COMPRESSED_RGBA_PVRTC_4BPPV1_IMG:
1960 case GL_COMPRESSED_RGBA_PVRTC_2BPPV1_IMG:
1961 if (!context->getExtensions().compressedTexturePVRTC)
1962 {
1963 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kEnumNotSupported);
1964 return false;
1965 }
1966 break;
1967 case GL_COMPRESSED_SRGB_PVRTC_2BPPV1_EXT:
1968 case GL_COMPRESSED_SRGB_PVRTC_4BPPV1_EXT:
1969 case GL_COMPRESSED_SRGB_ALPHA_PVRTC_2BPPV1_EXT:
1970 case GL_COMPRESSED_SRGB_ALPHA_PVRTC_4BPPV1_EXT:
1971 if (!context->getExtensions().compressedTexturePVRTCsRGB)
1972 {
1973 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kEnumNotSupported);
1974 return false;
1975 }
1976 break;
1977 case GL_RGBA32F_EXT:
1978 case GL_RGB32F_EXT:
1979 case GL_ALPHA32F_EXT:
1980 case GL_LUMINANCE32F_EXT:
1981 case GL_LUMINANCE_ALPHA32F_EXT:
1982 if (!context->getExtensions().textureFloatOES)
1983 {
1984 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kEnumNotSupported);
1985 return false;
1986 }
1987 break;
1988 case GL_RGBA16F_EXT:
1989 case GL_RGB16F_EXT:
1990 case GL_ALPHA16F_EXT:
1991 case GL_LUMINANCE16F_EXT:
1992 case GL_LUMINANCE_ALPHA16F_EXT:
1993 if (!context->getExtensions().textureHalfFloat)
1994 {
1995 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kEnumNotSupported);
1996 return false;
1997 }
1998 break;
1999 case GL_R8_EXT:
2000 case GL_RG8_EXT:
2001 if (!context->getExtensions().textureRG)
2002 {
2003 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kEnumNotSupported);
2004 return false;
2005 }
2006 break;
2007 case GL_R16F_EXT:
2008 case GL_RG16F_EXT:
2009 if (!context->getExtensions().textureRG || !context->getExtensions().textureHalfFloat)
2010 {
2011 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kEnumNotSupported);
2012 return false;
2013 }
2014 break;
2015 case GL_R32F_EXT:
2016 case GL_RG32F_EXT:
2017 if (!context->getExtensions().textureRG || !context->getExtensions().textureFloatOES)
2018 {
2019 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kEnumNotSupported);
2020 return false;
2021 }
2022 break;
2023 case GL_DEPTH_COMPONENT16:
2024 case GL_DEPTH_COMPONENT32_OES:
2025 if (!(context->getExtensions().depthTextureAny()))
2026 {
2027 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kEnumNotSupported);
2028 return false;
2029 }
2030
2031 switch (target)
2032 {
2033 case TextureType::_2D:
2034 break;
2035 case TextureType::CubeMap:
2036 if (!context->getExtensions().depthTextureCubeMapOES)
2037 {
2038 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kInvalidTextureTarget);
2039 return false;
2040 }
2041 break;
2042 default:
2043 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kInvalidTextureTarget);
2044 return false;
2045 }
2046
2047 // ANGLE_depth_texture only supports 1-level textures
2048 if (!context->getExtensions().depthTextureOES)
2049 {
2050 if (levels != 1)
2051 {
2052 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kInvalidMipLevels);
2053 return false;
2054 }
2055 }
2056 break;
2057 case GL_DEPTH24_STENCIL8_OES:
2058 if (!(context->getExtensions().depthTextureANGLE ||
2059 ((context->getExtensions().packedDepthStencilOES ||
2060 context->getExtensions().depthTextureCubeMapOES) &&
2061 context->getExtensions().textureStorage)))
2062 {
2063 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kEnumNotSupported);
2064 return false;
2065 }
2066
2067 switch (target)
2068 {
2069 case TextureType::_2D:
2070 break;
2071 case TextureType::CubeMap:
2072 if (!context->getExtensions().depthTextureCubeMapOES)
2073 {
2074 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kInvalidTextureTarget);
2075 return false;
2076 }
2077 break;
2078 default:
2079 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kInvalidTextureTarget);
2080 return false;
2081 }
2082
2083 if (!context->getExtensions().packedDepthStencilOES &&
2084 !context->getExtensions().depthTextureCubeMapOES)
2085 {
2086 // ANGLE_depth_texture only supports 1-level textures
2087 if (levels != 1)
2088 {
2089 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kInvalidMipLevels);
2090 return false;
2091 }
2092 }
2093 break;
2094
2095 default:
2096 break;
2097 }
2098
2099 Texture *texture = context->getTextureByType(target);
2100 if (!texture || texture->id().value == 0)
2101 {
2102 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kMissingTexture);
2103 return false;
2104 }
2105
2106 if (texture->getImmutableFormat())
2107 {
2108 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kTextureIsImmutable);
2109 return false;
2110 }
2111
2112 return true;
2113}

2731
2732bool ValidateBlitFramebufferANGLE(const Context *context,
2733 GLint srcX0,
2734 GLint srcY0,
2735 GLint srcX1,
2736 GLint srcY1,
2737 GLint dstX0,
2738 GLint dstY0,
2739 GLint dstX1,
2740 GLint dstY1,
2741 GLbitfield mask,
2742 GLenum filter)
2743{
2744 if (!context->getExtensions().framebufferBlit)
2745 {
2746 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kBlitExtensionNotAvailable);
2747 return false;
2748 }
2749
2750 if (srcX1 - srcX0 != dstX1 - dstX0 || srcY1 - srcY0 != dstY1 - dstY0)
2751 {
2752 // TODO(jmadill): Determine if this should be available on other implementations.
2753 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kBlitExtensionScaleOrFlip);
2754 return false;
2755 }
2756
2757 if (filter == GL_LINEAR)
2758 {
2759 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kBlitExtensionLinear);
2760 return false;
2761 }
2762
2763 Framebuffer *readFramebuffer = context->getState().getReadFramebuffer();
2764 Framebuffer *drawFramebuffer = context->getState().getDrawFramebuffer();
2765
2766 if (mask & GL_COLOR_BUFFER_BIT)
2767 {
2768 const FramebufferAttachment *readColorAttachment =
2769 readFramebuffer->getReadColorAttachment();
2770 const FramebufferAttachment *drawColorAttachment =
2771 drawFramebuffer->getFirstColorAttachment();
2772
2773 if (readColorAttachment && drawColorAttachment)
2774 {
2775 if (!(readColorAttachment->type() == GL_TEXTURE &&
2776 (readColorAttachment->getTextureImageIndex().getType() == TextureType::_2D ||
2777 readColorAttachment->getTextureImageIndex().getType() ==
2778 TextureType::Rectangle)) &&
2779 readColorAttachment->type() != GL_RENDERBUFFER &&
2780 readColorAttachment->type() != GL_FRAMEBUFFER_DEFAULT)
2781 {
2782 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION,
2783 kBlitExtensionFromInvalidAttachmentType);
2784 return false;
2785 }
2786
2787 for (size_t drawbufferIdx = 0;
2788 drawbufferIdx < drawFramebuffer->getDrawbufferStateCount(); ++drawbufferIdx)
2789 {
2790 const FramebufferAttachment *attachment =
2791 drawFramebuffer->getDrawBuffer(drawbufferIdx);
2792 if (attachment)
2793 {
2794 if (!(attachment->type() == GL_TEXTURE &&
2795 (attachment->getTextureImageIndex().getType() == TextureType::_2D ||
2796 attachment->getTextureImageIndex().getType() ==
2797 TextureType::Rectangle)) &&
2798 attachment->type() != GL_RENDERBUFFER &&
2799 attachment->type() != GL_FRAMEBUFFER_DEFAULT)
2800 {
2801 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION,
2802 kBlitExtensionToInvalidAttachmentType);
2803 return false;
2804 }
2805
2806 // Return an error if the destination formats do not match
2807 if (!Format::EquivalentForBlit(attachment->getFormat(),
2808 readColorAttachment->getFormat()))
2809 {
2810 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION,
2811 kBlitExtensionFormatMismatch);
2812 return false;
2813 }
2814 }
2815 }
2816
2817 GLint samples = readFramebuffer->getSamples(context);
2818 if (samples != 0 &&
2819 IsPartialBlit(context, readColorAttachment, drawColorAttachment, srcX0, srcY0,
2820 srcX1, srcY1, dstX0, dstY0, dstX1, dstY1))
2821 {
2822 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION,
2823 kBlitExtensionMultisampledWholeBufferBlit);
2824 return false;
2825 }
2826 }
2827 }
2828
2829 GLenum masks[] = {GL_DEPTH_BUFFER_BIT, GL_STENCIL_BUFFER_BIT};
2830 GLenum attachments[] = {GL_DEPTH_ATTACHMENT, GL_STENCIL_ATTACHMENT};
2831 for (size_t i = 0; i < 2; i++)
2832 {
2833 if (mask & masks[i])
2834 {
2835 const FramebufferAttachment *readBuffer =
2836 readFramebuffer->getAttachment(context, attachments[i]);
2837 const FramebufferAttachment *drawBuffer =
2838 drawFramebuffer->getAttachment(context, attachments[i]);
2839
2840 if (readBuffer && drawBuffer)
2841 {
2842 if (IsPartialBlit(context, readBuffer, drawBuffer, srcX0, srcY0, srcX1, srcY1,
2843 dstX0, dstY0, dstX1, dstY1))
2844 {
2845 // only whole-buffer copies are permitted
2846 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION,
2847 kBlitExtensionDepthStencilWholeBufferBlit);
2848 return false;
2849 }
2850
2851 if (readBuffer->getResourceSamples() != 0 || drawBuffer->getResourceSamples() != 0)
2852 {
2853 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION,
2854 kBlitExtensionMultisampledDepthOrStencil);
2855 return false;
2856 }
2857 }
2858 }
2859 }
2860
2861 return ValidateBlitFramebufferParameters(context, srcX0, srcY0, srcX1, srcY1, dstX0, dstY0,
2862 dstX1, dstY1, mask, filter);
2863}
2864
2865bool ValidateClear(const Context *context, GLbitfield mask)
2866{
2867 Framebuffer *fbo = context->getState().getDrawFramebuffer();
2868 const Extensions &extensions = context->getExtensions();
2869
2870 if (!ValidateFramebufferComplete(context, fbo))
2871 {
2872 return false;
2873 }
2874
2875 if ((mask & ~(GL_COLOR_BUFFER_BIT | GL_DEPTH_BUFFER_BIT | GL_STENCIL_BUFFER_BIT)) != 0)
2876 {
2877 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kInvalidClearMask);
2878 return false;
2879 }
2880
2881 if (extensions.webglCompatibility && (mask & GL_COLOR_BUFFER_BIT) != 0)
2882 {
2883 constexpr GLenum validComponentTypes[] = {GL_FLOAT, GL_UNSIGNED_NORMALIZED,
2884 GL_SIGNED_NORMALIZED};
2885
2886 for (GLuint drawBufferIdx = 0; drawBufferIdx < fbo->getDrawbufferStateCount();
2887 drawBufferIdx++)
2888 {
2889 if (!ValidateWebGLFramebufferAttachmentClearType(
2890 context, drawBufferIdx, validComponentTypes, ArraySize(validComponentTypes)))
2891 {
2892 return false;
2893 }
2894 }
2895 }
2896
2897 if ((extensions.multiview || extensions.multiview2) && extensions.disjointTimerQuery)
2898 {
2899 const State &state = context->getState();
2900 Framebuffer *framebuffer = state.getDrawFramebuffer();
2901 if (framebuffer->getNumViews() > 1 && state.isQueryActive(QueryType::TimeElapsed))
2902 {
2903 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kMultiviewTimerQuery);
2904 return false;
2905 }
2906 }
2907
2908 return true;
2909}

3233bool ValidateMapBufferOES(const Context *context, BufferBinding target, GLenum access)
3234{
3235 if (!context->getExtensions().mapBufferOES)
3236 {
3237 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kExtensionNotEnabled);
3238 return false;
3239 }
3240
3241 if (!context->isValidBufferBinding(target))
3242 {
3243 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kInvalidBufferTypes);
3244 return false;
3245 }
3246
3247 Buffer *buffer = context->getState().getTargetBuffer(target);
3248
3249 if (buffer == nullptr)
3250 {
3251 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kBufferNotMappable);
3252 return false;
3253 }
3254
3255 if (access != GL_WRITE_ONLY_OES)
3256 {
3257 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kInvalidAccessBits);
3258 return false;
3259 }
3260
3261 // Though there is no explicit mention of an interaction between GL_EXT_buffer_storage
3262 // and GL_OES_mapbuffer extension, allow it as long as the access type of glMapBufferOES
3263 // is compatible with the buffer's usage flags specified during glBufferStorageEXT
3264 if (buffer->isImmutable() && (buffer->getStorageExtUsageFlags() & GL_MAP_WRITE_BIT) == 0)
3265 {
3266 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kBufferNotMappable);
3267 return false;
3268 }
3269
3270 if (buffer->isMapped())
3271 {
3272 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kBufferAlreadyMapped);
3273 return false;
3274 }
3275
3276 return ValidateMapBufferBase(context, target);
3277}

3305bool ValidateMapBufferBase(const Context *context, BufferBinding target)
3306{
3307 Buffer *buffer = context->getState().getTargetBuffer(target);
3308 ASSERT(buffer != nullptr);
3309
3310 // Check if this buffer is currently being used as a transform feedback output buffer
3311 if (context->getState().isTransformFeedbackActive())
3312 {
3313 TransformFeedback *transformFeedback = context->getState().getCurrentTransformFeedback();
3314 for (size_t i = 0; i < transformFeedback->getIndexedBufferCount(); i++)
3315 {
3316 const auto &transformFeedbackBuffer = transformFeedback->getIndexedBuffer(i);
3317 if (transformFeedbackBuffer.get() == buffer)
3318 {
3319 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kBufferBoundForTransformFeedback);
3320 return false;
3321 }
3322 }
3323 }
3324
3325 if (context->getExtensions().webglCompatibility &&
3326 buffer->isBoundForTransformFeedbackAndOtherUse())
3327 {
3328 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kBufferBoundForTransformFeedback);
3329 return false;
3330 }
3331
3332 return true;
3333}

3353{

3363 return false;

3391 return false;
3392 }

3419bool ValidateCopyTextureCHROMIUM(const Context *context,
3420 TextureID sourceId,
3421 GLint sourceLevel,
3422 TextureTarget destTarget,
3423 TextureID destId,
3424 GLint destLevel,
3425 GLint internalFormat,
3426 GLenum destType,
3427 GLboolean unpackFlipY,
3428 GLboolean unpackPremultiplyAlpha,
3429 GLboolean unpackUnmultiplyAlpha)
3430{
3431 if (!context->getExtensions().copyTexture)
3432 {
3433 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kExtensionNotEnabled);
3434 return false;
3435 }
3436
3437 const Texture *source = context->getTexture(sourceId);
3438 if (source == nullptr)
3439 {
3440 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kInvalidSourceTexture);
3441 return false;
3442 }
3443
3444 if (!IsValidCopyTextureSourceTarget(context, source->getType()))
3445 {
3446 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kInvalidInternalFormat);
3447 return false;
3448 }
3449
3450 TextureType sourceType = source->getType();
3451 ASSERT(sourceType != TextureType::CubeMap);
3452 TextureTarget sourceTarget = NonCubeTextureTypeToTarget(sourceType);
3453
3454 if (!IsValidCopyTextureSourceLevel(context, sourceType, sourceLevel))
3455 {
3456 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kInvalidSourceTextureLevel);
3457 return false;
3458 }
3459
3460 GLsizei sourceWidth = static_cast<GLsizei>(source->getWidth(sourceTarget, sourceLevel));
3461 GLsizei sourceHeight = static_cast<GLsizei>(source->getHeight(sourceTarget, sourceLevel));
3462 if (sourceWidth == 0 || sourceHeight == 0)
3463 {
3464 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kInvalidInternalFormat);
3465 return false;
3466 }
3467
3468 const InternalFormat &sourceFormat = *source->getFormat(sourceTarget, sourceLevel).info;
3469 if (!IsValidCopyTextureSourceInternalFormatEnum(sourceFormat.internalFormat))
3470 {
3471 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kInvalidSourceTextureInternalFormat);
3472 return false;
3473 }
3474
3475 if (!IsValidCopyTextureDestinationTargetEnum(context, destTarget))
3476 {
3477 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kInvalidTextureTarget);
3478 return false;
3479 }
3480
3481 const Texture *dest = context->getTexture(destId);
3482 if (dest == nullptr)
3483 {
3484 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kInvalidDestinationTexture);
3485 return false;
3486 }
3487
3488 if (!IsValidCopyTextureDestinationTarget(context, dest->getType(), destTarget))
3489 {
3490 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kInvalidDestinationTextureType);
3491 return false;
3492 }
3493
3494 if (!IsValidCopyTextureDestinationLevel(context, dest->getType(), destLevel, sourceWidth,
3495 sourceHeight, false))
3496 {
3497 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kInvalidMipLevel);
3498 return false;
3499 }
3500
3501 if (!IsValidCopyTextureDestinationFormatType(context, internalFormat, destType))
3502 {
3503 return false;
3504 }
3505
3506 if (dest->getType() == TextureType::CubeMap && sourceWidth != sourceHeight)
3507 {
3508 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kCubemapFacesEqualDimensions);
3509 return false;
3510 }
3511
3512 if (dest->getImmutableFormat())
3513 {
3514 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kDestinationImmutable);
3515 return false;
3516 }
3517
3518 return true;

3744bool ValidateBufferData(const Context *context,
3745 BufferBinding target,
3746 GLsizeiptr size,
3747 const void *data,
3748 BufferUsage usage)
3749{
3750 if (size < 0)
3751 {
3752 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kNegativeSize);
3753 return false;
3754 }
3755
3756 switch (usage)
3757 {
3758 case BufferUsage::StreamDraw:
3759 case BufferUsage::StaticDraw:
3760 case BufferUsage::DynamicDraw:
3761 break;
3762
3763 case BufferUsage::StreamRead:
3764 case BufferUsage::StaticRead:
3765 case BufferUsage::DynamicRead:
3766 case BufferUsage::StreamCopy:
3767 case BufferUsage::StaticCopy:
3768 case BufferUsage::DynamicCopy:
3769 if (context->getClientMajorVersion() < 3)
3770 {
3771 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kInvalidBufferUsage);
3772 return false;
3773 }
3774 break;
3775
3776 default:
3777 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kInvalidBufferUsage);
3778 return false;
3779 }
3780
3781 if (!context->isValidBufferBinding(target))
3782 {
3783 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kInvalidBufferTypes);
3784 return false;
3785 }
3786
3787 Buffer *buffer = context->getState().getTargetBuffer(target);
3788
3789 if (!buffer)
3790 {
3791 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kBufferNotBound);
3792 return false;
3793 }
3794
3795 if (context->getExtensions().webglCompatibility &&
3796 buffer->isBoundForTransformFeedbackAndOtherUse())
3797 {
3798 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kBufferBoundForTransformFeedback);
3799 return false;
3800 }
3801
3802 if (buffer->isImmutable())
3803 {
3804 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kBufferImmutable);
3805 return false;
3806 }
3807
3808 return true;
3809}
3810
3811bool ValidateBufferSubData(const Context *context,
3812 BufferBinding target,
3813 GLintptr offset,
3814 GLsizeiptr size,
3815 const void *data)
3816{
3817 if (size < 0)
3818 {
3819 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kNegativeSize);
3820 return false;
3821 }
3822
3823 if (offset < 0)
3824 {
3825 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kNegativeOffset);
3826 return false;
3827 }
3828
3829 if (!context->isValidBufferBinding(target))
3830 {
3831 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kInvalidBufferTypes);
3832 return false;
3833 }
3834
3835 Buffer *buffer = context->getState().getTargetBuffer(target);
3836
3837 if (!buffer)
3838 {
3839 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kBufferNotBound);
3840 return false;
3841 }
3842
3843 if (buffer->isMapped())
3844 {
3845 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kBufferMapped);
3846 return false;
3847 }
3848
3849 if (context->getExtensions().webglCompatibility &&
3850 buffer->isBoundForTransformFeedbackAndOtherUse())
3851 {
3852 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kBufferBoundForTransformFeedback);
3853 return false;
3854 }
3855
3856 if (buffer->isImmutable() &&
3857 (buffer->getStorageExtUsageFlags() & GL_DYNAMIC_STORAGE_BIT_EXT) == 0)
3858 {
3859 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kBufferNotUpdatable);
3860 return false;
3861 }
3862
3863 // Check for possible overflow of size + offset
3864 angle::CheckedNumeric<size_t> checkedSize(size);
3865 checkedSize += offset;
3866 if (!checkedSize.IsValid())
3867 {
3868 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kParamOverflow);
3869 return false;
3870 }
3871
3872 if (size + offset > buffer->getSize())
3873 {
3874 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kInsufficientBufferSize);
3875 return false;
3876 }
3877
3878 return true;
3879}

4208bool ValidateRenderbufferStorageMultisampleANGLE(const Context *context,
4209 GLenum target,
4210 GLsizei samples,
4211 GLenum internalformat,
4212 GLsizei width,
4213 GLsizei height)
4214{
4215 if (!context->getExtensions().framebufferMultisample)
4216 {
4217 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kExtensionNotEnabled);
4218 return false;
4219 }
4220
4221 // ANGLE_framebuffer_multisample states that the value of samples must be less than or equal
4222 // to MAX_SAMPLES_ANGLE (Context::getCaps().maxSamples) otherwise GL_INVALID_VALUE is
4223 // generated.
4224 if (samples > context->getCaps().maxSamples)
4225 {
4226 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kSamplesOutOfRange);
4227 return false;
4228 }
4229
4230 // ANGLE_framebuffer_multisample states GL_OUT_OF_MEMORY is generated on a failure to create
4231 // the specified storage. This is different than ES 3.0 in which a sample number higher
4232 // than the maximum sample number supported by this format generates a GL_INVALID_VALUE.
4233 // The TextureCaps::getMaxSamples method is only guarenteed to be valid when the context is ES3.
4234 if (context->getClientMajorVersion() >= 3)
4235 {
4236 const TextureCaps &formatCaps = context->getTextureCaps().get(internalformat);
4237 if (static_cast<GLuint>(samples) > formatCaps.getMaxSamples())
4238 {
4239 context->validationError(GL_OUT_OF_MEMORY, kSamplesOutOfRange);
4240 return false;
4241 }
4242 }
4243
4244 return ValidateRenderbufferStorageParametersBase(context, target, samples, internalformat,
4245 width, height);
4246}

4643 const GLint *precision)
4644{
4645 switch (shadertype)
4646 {
4647 case GL_VERTEX_SHADER:
4648 case GL_FRAGMENT_SHADER:
4649 break;
4650 case GL_COMPUTE_SHADER:
4651 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kUnimplementedComputeShaderPrecision);
4652 return false;
4653 default:
4654 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kInvalidShaderType);
4655 return false;
4656 }
4657
4658 switch (precisiontype)
4659 {
4660 case GL_LOW_FLOAT:
4661 case GL_MEDIUM_FLOAT:
4662 case GL_HIGH_FLOAT:
4663 case GL_LOW_INT:
4664 case GL_MEDIUM_INT:
4665 case GL_HIGH_INT:
4666 break;
4667
4668 default:
4669 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kInvalidPrecision);
4670 return false;
4671 }
4672
4673 return true;
4674}

4697bool ValidateGetUniformLocation(const Context *context, ShaderProgramID program, const GLchar *name)
4698{
4699 if (strstr(name, "gl_") == name)
4700 {
4701 return false;
4702 }
4703
4704 // The WebGL spec (section 6.20) disallows strings containing invalid ESSL characters for
4705 // shader-related entry points
4706 if (context->getExtensions().webglCompatibility && !IsValidESSLString(name, strlen(name)))
4707 {
4708 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kInvalidNameCharacters);
4709 return false;
4710 }
4711
4712 Program *programObject = GetValidProgram(context, program);
4713
4714 if (!programObject)
4715 {
4716 return false;
4717 }
4718
4719 if (!programObject->isLinked())
4720 {
4721 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kProgramNotLinked);
4722 return false;
4723 }
4724
4725 return true;
4726}

4728bool ValidateHint(const Context *context, GLenum target, GLenum mode)
4729{
4730 switch (mode)
4731 {
4732 case GL_FASTEST:
4733 case GL_NICEST:
4734 case GL_DONT_CARE:
4735 break;
4736
4737 default:
4738 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kEnumNotSupported);
4739 return false;
4740 }
4741
4742 switch (target)
4743 {
4744 case GL_GENERATE_MIPMAP_HINT:
4745 break;
4746
4747 case GL_TEXTURE_FILTERING_HINT_CHROMIUM:
4748 if (!context->getExtensions().textureFilteringCHROMIUM)
4749 {
4750 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kEnumNotSupported);
4751 return false;
4752 }
4753 break;
4754
4755 case GL_FRAGMENT_SHADER_DERIVATIVE_HINT:
4756 if (context->getClientVersion() < ES_3_0 &&
4757 !context->getExtensions().standardDerivativesOES)
4758 {
4759 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kEnumNotSupported);
4760 return false;
4761 }
4762 break;
4763
4764 case GL_PERSPECTIVE_CORRECTION_HINT:
4765 case GL_POINT_SMOOTH_HINT:
4766 case GL_LINE_SMOOTH_HINT:
4767 case GL_FOG_HINT:
4768 if (context->getClientMajorVersion() >= 2)
4769 {
4770 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kEnumNotSupported);
4771 return false;
4772 }
4773 break;
4774
4775 default:
4776 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kEnumNotSupported);
4777 return false;
4778 }
4779
4780 return true;
4781}

4813bool ValidatePixelStorei(const Context *context, GLenum pname, GLint param)
4814{
4815 if (context->getClientMajorVersion() < 3)
4816 {
4817 switch (pname)
4818 {
4819 case GL_UNPACK_IMAGE_HEIGHT:
4820 case GL_UNPACK_SKIP_IMAGES:
4821 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kInvalidPname);
4822 return false;
4823
4824 case GL_UNPACK_ROW_LENGTH:
4825 case GL_UNPACK_SKIP_ROWS:
4826 case GL_UNPACK_SKIP_PIXELS:
4827 if (!context->getExtensions().unpackSubimage)
4828 {
4829 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kInvalidPname);
4830 return false;
4831 }
4832 break;
4833
4834 case GL_PACK_ROW_LENGTH:
4835 case GL_PACK_SKIP_ROWS:
4836 case GL_PACK_SKIP_PIXELS:
4837 if (!context->getExtensions().packSubimage)
4838 {
4839 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kInvalidPname);
4840 return false;
4841 }
4842 break;
4843 }
4844 }
4845
4846 if (param < 0)
4847 {
4848 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kNegativeParam);
4849 return false;
4850 }
4851
4852 switch (pname)
4853 {
4854 case GL_UNPACK_ALIGNMENT:
4855 if (param != 1 && param != 2 && param != 4 && param != 8)
4856 {
4857 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kInvalidUnpackAlignment);
4858 return false;
4859 }
4860 break;
4861
4862 case GL_PACK_ALIGNMENT:
4863 if (param != 1 && param != 2 && param != 4 && param != 8)
4864 {
4865 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kInvalidUnpackAlignment);
4866 return false;
4867 }
4868 break;
4869
4870 case GL_PACK_REVERSE_ROW_ORDER_ANGLE:
4871 if (!context->getExtensions().packReverseRowOrder)
4872 {
4873 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kEnumNotSupported);
4874 }
4875 break;
4876
4877 case GL_UNPACK_ROW_LENGTH:
4878 case GL_UNPACK_IMAGE_HEIGHT:
4879 case GL_UNPACK_SKIP_IMAGES:
4880 case GL_UNPACK_SKIP_ROWS:
4881 case GL_UNPACK_SKIP_PIXELS:
4882 case GL_PACK_ROW_LENGTH:
4883 case GL_PACK_SKIP_ROWS:
4884 case GL_PACK_SKIP_PIXELS:
4885 break;
4886
4887 default:
4888 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kEnumNotSupported);
4889 return false;
4890 }
4891
4892 return true;
4893}
