5416bool ValidateFramebufferTexture2D(const Context *context,
5417 GLenum target,
5418 GLenum attachment,
5419 TextureTarget textarget,
5420 TextureID texture,
5421 GLint level)
5422{
5423 // Attachments are required to be bound to level 0 without ES3 or the GL_OES_fbo_render_mipmap
5424 // extension
5425 if (context->getClientMajorVersion() < 3 && !context->getExtensions().fboRenderMipmapOES &&
5426 level != 0)
5427 {
5428 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kInvalidFramebufferTextureLevel);
5429 return false;
5430 }
5431
5432 if (!ValidateFramebufferTextureBase(context, target, attachment, texture, level))
5433 {
5434 return false;
5435 }
5436
5437 if (texture.value != 0)
5438 {
5439 Texture *tex = context->getTexture(texture);
5440 ASSERT(tex);
5441
5442 const Caps &caps = context->getCaps();
5443
5444 switch (textarget)
5445 {
5446 case TextureTarget::_2D:
5447 {
5448 if (level > log2(caps.max2DTextureSize))
5449 {
5450 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kInvalidMipLevel);
5451 return false;
5452 }
5453 if (tex->getType() != TextureType::_2D)
5454 {
5455 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kInvalidTextureTarget);
5456 return false;
5457 }
5458 }
5459 break;
5460
5461 case TextureTarget::Rectangle:
5462 {
5463 if (level != 0)
5464 {
5465 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kInvalidMipLevel);
5466 return false;
5467 }
5468 if (tex->getType() != TextureType::Rectangle)
5469 {
5470 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kTextureTargetMismatch);
5471 return false;
5472 }
5473 }
5474 break;
5475
5476 case TextureTarget::CubeMapNegativeX:
5477 case TextureTarget::CubeMapNegativeY:
5478 case TextureTarget::CubeMapNegativeZ:
5479 case TextureTarget::CubeMapPositiveX:
5480 case TextureTarget::CubeMapPositiveY:
5481 case TextureTarget::CubeMapPositiveZ:
5482 {
5483 if (level > log2(caps.maxCubeMapTextureSize))
5484 {
5485 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kInvalidMipLevel);
5486 return false;
5487 }
5488 if (tex->getType() != TextureType::CubeMap)
5489 {
5490 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kTextureTargetMismatch);
5491 return false;
5492 }
5493 }
5494 break;
5495
5496 case TextureTarget::_2DMultisample:
5497 {
5498 if (context->getClientVersion() < ES_3_1 &&
5499 !context->getExtensions().textureMultisample)
5500 {
5501 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION,
5502 kMultisampleTextureExtensionOrES31Required);
5503 return false;
5504 }
5505
5506 if (level != 0)
5507 {
5508 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kLevelNotZero);
5509 return false;
5510 }
5511 if (tex->getType() != TextureType::_2DMultisample)
5512 {
5513 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kTextureTargetMismatch);
5514 return false;
5515 }
5516 }
5517 break;
5518
5519 default:
5520 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kInvalidTextureTarget);
5521 return false;
5522 }
5523 }
5524
5525 return true;
5526}
5527
5528bool ValidateFramebufferTexture3DOES(const Context *context,
5529 GLenum target,
5530 GLenum attachment,
5531 TextureTarget textargetPacked,
5532 TextureID texture,
5533 GLint level,
5534 GLint zoffset)
5535{
5536 // We don't call into a base ValidateFramebufferTexture3D here because
5537 // it doesn't exist for OpenGL ES. This function is replaced by
5538 // FramebufferTextureLayer in ES 3.x, which has broader support.
5539 if (!context->getExtensions().texture3DOES)
5540 {
5541 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kExtensionNotEnabled);
5542 return false;
5543 }
5544
5545 // Attachments are required to be bound to level 0 without ES3 or the
5546 // GL_OES_fbo_render_mipmap extension
5547 if (context->getClientMajorVersion() < 3 && !context->getExtensions().fboRenderMipmapOES &&
5548 level != 0)
5549 {
5550 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kInvalidFramebufferTextureLevel);
5551 return false;
5552 }
5553
5554 if (!ValidateFramebufferTextureBase(context, target, attachment, texture, level))
5555 {
5556 return false;
5557 }
5558
5559 if (texture.value != 0)
5560 {
5561 Texture *tex = context->getTexture(texture);
5562 ASSERT(tex);
5563
5564 const Caps &caps = context->getCaps();
5565
5566 switch (textargetPacked)
5567 {
5568 case TextureTarget::_3D:
5569 {
5570 if (level > log2(caps.max3DTextureSize))
5571 {
5572 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kInvalidMipLevel);
5573 return false;
5574 }
5575 if (zoffset >= caps.max3DTextureSize)
5576 {
5577 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kInvalidZOffset);
5578 return false;
5579 }
5580 if (tex->getType() != TextureType::_3D)
5581 {
5582 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kInvalidTextureType);
5583 return false;
5584 }
5585 }
5586 break;
5587
5588 default:
5589 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kInvalidTextureTarget);
5590 return false;
5591 }
5592 }
5593
5594 return true;
5595}

5616
5617bool ValidateGenerateMipmap(const Context *context, TextureType target)
5618{
5619 if (!ValidTextureTarget(context, target))
5620 {
5621 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kInvalidTextureTarget);
5622 return false;
5623 }
5624
5625 Texture *texture = context->getTextureByType(target);
5626
5627 if (texture == nullptr)
5628 {
5629 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kTextureNotBound);
5630 return false;
5631 }
5632
5633 const GLuint effectiveBaseLevel = texture->getTextureState().getEffectiveBaseLevel();
5634
5635 // This error isn't spelled out in the spec in a very explicit way, but we interpret the spec so
5636 // that out-of-range base level has a non-color-renderable / non-texture-filterable format.
5637 if (effectiveBaseLevel >= IMPLEMENTATION_MAX_TEXTURE_LEVELS)
5638 {
5639 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kBaseLevelOutOfRange);
5640 return false;
5641 }
5642
5643 TextureTarget baseTarget = (target == TextureType::CubeMap)
5644 ? TextureTarget::CubeMapPositiveX
5645 : NonCubeTextureTypeToTarget(target);
5646 const auto &format = *(texture->getFormat(baseTarget, effectiveBaseLevel).info);
5647 if (format.sizedInternalFormat == GL_NONE || format.compressed || format.depthBits > 0 ||
5648 format.stencilBits > 0)
5649 {
5650 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kGenerateMipmapNotAllowed);
5651 return false;
5652 }
5653
5654 // GenerateMipmap accepts formats that are unsized or both color renderable and filterable.
5655 bool formatUnsized = !format.sized;
5656 bool formatColorRenderableAndFilterable =
5657 format.filterSupport(context->getClientVersion(), context->getExtensions()) &&
5658 format.textureAttachmentSupport(context->getClientVersion(), context->getExtensions());
5659 if (!formatUnsized && !formatColorRenderableAndFilterable)
5660 {
5661 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kGenerateMipmapNotAllowed);
5662 return false;
5663 }
5664
5665 // GL_EXT_sRGB adds an unsized SRGB (no alpha) format which has explicitly disabled mipmap
5666 // generation
5667 if (format.colorEncoding == GL_SRGB && format.format == GL_RGB)
5668 {
5669 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kGenerateMipmapNotAllowed);
5670 return false;
5671 }
5672
5673 // According to the OpenGL extension spec EXT_sRGB.txt, EXT_SRGB is based on ES 2.0 and
5674 // generateMipmap is not allowed if texture format is SRGB_EXT or SRGB_ALPHA_EXT.
5675 if (context->getClientVersion() < Version(3, 0) && format.colorEncoding == GL_SRGB)
5676 {
5677 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kGenerateMipmapNotAllowed);
5678 return false;
5679 }
5680
5681 // Non-power of 2 ES2 check
5682 if (context->getClientVersion() < Version(3, 0) && !context->getExtensions().textureNPOTOES &&
5683 (!isPow2(static_cast<int>(texture->getWidth(baseTarget, 0))) ||
5684 !isPow2(static_cast<int>(texture->getHeight(baseTarget, 0)))))
5685 {
5686 ASSERT(target == TextureType::_2D || target == TextureType::Rectangle ||
5687 target == TextureType::CubeMap);
5688 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kTextureNotPow2);
5689 return false;
5690 }
5691
5692 // Cube completeness check
5693 if (target == TextureType::CubeMap && !texture->getTextureState().isCubeComplete())
5694 {
5695 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kCubemapIncomplete);
5696 return false;
5697 }
5698
5699 if (context->getExtensions().webglCompatibility &&
5700 (texture->getWidth(baseTarget, effectiveBaseLevel) == 0 ||
5701 texture->getHeight(baseTarget, effectiveBaseLevel) == 0))
5702 {
5703 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kGenerateMipmapZeroSize);
5704 return false;
5705 }
5706
5707 return true;
5708}

5911{

5914 Program *programObject = context->getProgramResolveLink(program);

5920 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kExpectedProgramName);
5921 return false;

5924 {
5925 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kInvalidProgramName);
5926 return false;

5930 {
5931 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kProgramNotLinked);

5934 }
5935 if (context->getState().isTransformFeedbackActiveUnpaused())
5936 {
5937 // ES 3.0.4 section 2.15 page 91
5938 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kTransformFeedbackUseProgram);
5939 return false;
5940 }
5941

6353bool ValidateFramebufferTexture2DMultisampleEXT(const Context *context,
6354 GLenum target,
6355 GLenum attachment,
6356 TextureTarget textarget,
6357 TextureID texture,
6358 GLint level,
6359 GLsizei samples)
6360{
6361 if (!context->getExtensions().multisampledRenderToTexture)
6362 {
6363 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kExtensionNotEnabled);
6364 return false;
6365 }
6366
6367 if (samples < 0)
6368 {
6369 return false;
6370 }
6371
6372 // EXT_multisampled_render_to_texture states that the value of samples
6373 // must be less than or equal to MAX_SAMPLES_EXT (Context::getCaps().maxSamples)
6374 // otherwise GL_INVALID_VALUE is generated.
6375 if (samples > context->getCaps().maxSamples)
6376 {
6377 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kSamplesOutOfRange);
6378 return false;
6379 }
6380
6381 // EXT_multisampled_render_to_texture returns INVALID_OPERATION when a sample number higher than
6382 // the maximum sample number supported by this format is passed.
6383 // The TextureCaps::getMaxSamples method is only guarenteed to be valid when the context is ES3.
6384 if (texture.value != 0 && context->getClientMajorVersion() >= 3)
6385 {
6386 Texture *tex = context->getTexture(texture);
6387 GLenum internalformat = tex->getFormat(textarget, level).info->internalFormat;
6388 const TextureCaps &formatCaps = context->getTextureCaps().get(internalformat);
6389 if (static_cast<GLuint>(samples) > formatCaps.getMaxSamples())
6390 {
6391 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kSamplesOutOfRange);
6392 return false;
6393 }
6394 }
6395
6396 if (!ValidateFramebufferTextureBase(context, target, attachment, texture, level))
6397 {
6398 return false;
6399 }
6400
6401 // Unless EXT_multisampled_render_to_texture2 is enabled, only color attachment 0 can be used.
6402 if (!context->getExtensions().multisampledRenderToTexture2 &&
6403 attachment != GL_COLOR_ATTACHMENT0)
6404 {
6405 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kInvalidAttachment);
6406 return false;
6407 }
6408
6409 if (!ValidTexture2DDestinationTarget(context, textarget))
6410 {
6411 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kInvalidTextureTarget);
6412 return false;
6413 }
6414
6415 return true;
6416}
6417
6418bool ValidateRenderbufferStorageMultisampleEXT(const Context *context,
6419 GLenum target,
6420 GLsizei samples,
6421 GLenum internalformat,
6422 GLsizei width,
6423 GLsizei height)
6424{
6425 if (!context->getExtensions().multisampledRenderToTexture)
6426 {
6427 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, kExtensionNotEnabled);
6428 return false;
6429 }
6430 if (!ValidateRenderbufferStorageParametersBase(context, target, samples, internalformat, width,
6431 height))
6432 {
6433 return false;
6434 }
6435
6436 // EXT_multisampled_render_to_texture states that the value of samples
6437 // must be less than or equal to MAX_SAMPLES_EXT (Context::getCaps().maxSamples)
6438 // otherwise GL_INVALID_VALUE is generated.
6439 if (samples > context->getCaps().maxSamples)
6440 {
6441 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_VALUE, kSamplesOutOfRange);
6442 return false;
6443 }
6444
6445 // EXT_multisampled_render_to_texture returns GL_OUT_OF_MEMORY on failure to create
6446 // the specified storage. This is different than ES 3.0 in which a sample number higher
6447 // than the maximum sample number supported by this format generates a GL_INVALID_VALUE.
6448 // The TextureCaps::getMaxSamples method is only guarenteed to be valid when the context is ES3.
6449 if (context->getClientMajorVersion() >= 3)
6450 {
6451 const TextureCaps &formatCaps = context->getTextureCaps().get(internalformat);
6452 if (static_cast<GLuint>(samples) > formatCaps.getMaxSamples())
6453 {
6454 context->validationError(GL_OUT_OF_MEMORY, kSamplesOutOfRange);
6455 return false;
6456 }
6457 }
6458
6459 return true;
6460}
6461
6462void RecordBindTextureTypeError(const Context *context, TextureType target)
6463{
6464 ASSERT(!context->getStateCache().isValidBindTextureType(target));
6465
6466 switch (target)
6467 {
6468 case TextureType::Rectangle:
6469 ASSERT(!context->getExtensions().textureRectangle);
6470 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kTextureRectangleNotSupported);
6471 break;
6472
6473 case TextureType::_3D:
6474 case TextureType::_2DArray:
6475 ASSERT(context->getClientMajorVersion() < 3);
6476 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kES3Required);
6477 break;
6478
6479 case TextureType::_2DMultisample:
6480 ASSERT(context->getClientVersion() < Version(3, 1) &&
6481 !context->getExtensions().textureMultisample);
6482 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kMultisampleTextureExtensionOrES31Required);
6483 break;
6484
6485 case TextureType::_2DMultisampleArray:
6486 ASSERT(!context->getExtensions().textureStorageMultisample2DArrayOES);
6487 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kMultisampleArrayExtensionRequired);
6488 break;
6489
6490 case TextureType::External:
6491 ASSERT(!context->getExtensions().eglImageExternalOES &&
6492 !context->getExtensions().eglStreamConsumerExternalNV);
6493 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kExternalTextureNotSupported);
6494 break;
6495
6496 case TextureType::VideoImage:
6497 ASSERT(!context->getExtensions().webglVideoTexture);
6498 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kExtensionNotEnabled);
6499 break;
6500
6501 default:
6502 context->validationError(GL_INVALID_ENUM, kInvalidTextureTarget);
6503 }
6504}
